10306  {
10307  public static void hermitianmatrixvectormultiply(complex[,] a,
10308  bool isupper,
10309  int i1,
10310  int i2,
10311  complex[] x,
10312  complex alpha,
10313  ref complex[] y,
10314  alglib.xparams _params)
10315  {
10316  int i = 0;
10317  int ba1 = 0;
10318  int by1 = 0;
10319  int by2 = 0;
10320  int bx1 = 0;
10321  int bx2 = 0;
10322  int n = 0;
10323  complex v = 0;
10324  int i_ = 0;
10325  int i1_ = 0;
10326 
10327  n = i2-i1+1;
10328  if( n<=0 )
10329  {
10330  return;
10331  }
10332 
10333  //
10334  // Let A = L + D + U, where
10335  // L is strictly lower triangular (main diagonal is zero)
10336  // D is diagonal
10337  // U is strictly upper triangular (main diagonal is zero)
10338  //
10339  // A*x = L*x + D*x + U*x
10340  //
10341  // Calculate D*x first
10342  //
10343  for(i=i1; i<=i2; i++)
10344  {
10345  y[i-i1+1] = a[i,i]*x[i-i1+1];
10346  }
10347 
10348  //
10349  // Add L*x + U*x
10350  //
10351  if( isupper )
10352  {
10353  for(i=i1; i<=i2-1; i++)
10354  {
10355 
10356  //
10357  // Add L*x to the result
10358  //
10359  v = x[i-i1+1];
10360  by1 = i-i1+2;
10361  by2 = n;
10362  ba1 = i+1;
10363  i1_ = (ba1) - (by1);
10364  for(i_=by1; i_<=by2;i_++)
10365  {
10366  y[i_] = y[i_] + v*math.conj(a[i,i_+i1_]);
10367  }
10368 
10369  //
10370  // Add U*x to the result
10371  //
10372  bx1 = i-i1+2;
10373  bx2 = n;
10374  ba1 = i+1;
10375  i1_ = (ba1)-(bx1);
10376  v = 0.0;
10377  for(i_=bx1; i_<=bx2;i_++)
10378  {
10379  v += x[i_]*a[i,i_+i1_];
10380  }
10381  y[i-i1+1] = y[i-i1+1]+v;
10382  }
10383  }
10384  else
10385  {
10386  for(i=i1+1; i<=i2; i++)
10387  {
10388 
10389  //
10390  // Add L*x to the result
10391  //
10392  bx1 = 1;
10393  bx2 = i-i1;
10394  ba1 = i1;
10395  i1_ = (ba1)-(bx1);
10396  v = 0.0;
10397  for(i_=bx1; i_<=bx2;i_++)
10398  {
10399  v += x[i_]*a[i,i_+i1_];
10400  }
10401  y[i-i1+1] = y[i-i1+1]+v;
10402 
10403  //
10404  // Add U*x to the result
10405  //
10406  v = x[i-i1+1];
10407  by1 = 1;
10408  by2 = i-i1;
10409  ba1 = i1;
10410  i1_ = (ba1) - (by1);
10411  for(i_=by1; i_<=by2;i_++)
10412  {
10413  y[i_] = y[i_] + v*math.conj(a[i,i_+i1_]);
10414  }
10415  }
10416  }
10417  for(i_=1; i_<=n;i_++)
10418  {
10419  y[i_] = alpha*y[i_];
10420  }
10421  }
10422

10424  public static void hermitianrank2update(ref complex[,] a,
10425  bool isupper,
10426  int i1,
10427  int i2,
10428  complex[] x,
10429  complex[] y,
10430  ref complex[] t,
10431  complex alpha,
10432  alglib.xparams _params)

10436  int tp2 = 0;

10444  {

10449  {

10451  }

10470  v = alpha*x[i+1-i1];
10471  for(i_=tp1; i_<=tp2;i_++)

10693  public static double vectornorm2(double[] x,
10694  int i1,
10695  int i2,
10696  alglib.xparams _params)
10697  {
10698  double result = 0;
10699  int n = 0;
10700  int ix = 0;
10701  double absxi = 0;
10702  double scl = 0;
10703  double ssq = 0;
10704 
10705  n = i2-i1+1;
10706  if( n<1 )
10707  {
10708  result = 0;
10709  return result;
10710  }
10711  if( n==1 )
10712  {
10713  result = Math.Abs(x[i1]);
10714  return result;
10715  }
10716  scl = 0;
10717  ssq = 1;
10718  for(ix=i1; ix<=i2; ix++)
10719  {
10720  if( (double)(x[ix])!=(double)(0) )
10721  {
10722  absxi = Math.Abs(x[ix]);
10723  if( (double)(scl)<(double)(absxi) )
10724  {
10725  ssq = 1+ssq*math.sqr(scl/absxi);
10726  scl = absxi;
10727  }
10728  else
10729  {
10730  ssq = ssq+math.sqr(absxi/scl);
10731  }
10732  }
10733  }
10734  result = scl*Math.Sqrt(ssq);
10735  return result;
10736  }

10950  public static void matrixvectormultiply(double[,] a,

10969  int i1_ = 0;
10970

10972  {
10973

10976  //

10978  {
10979  return;
10980  }
10981  alglib.ap.assert(j2-j1==ix2-ix1, "MatrixVectorMultiply: A and X dont match!");
10982  alglib.ap.assert(i2-i1==iy2-iy1, "MatrixVectorMultiply: A and Y dont match!");
10983

10986  //
10987  if( (double)(beta)==(double)(0) )
10988  {
10989  for(i=iy1; i<=iy2; i++)
10990  {
10991  y[i] = 0;
10992  }
10993  }
10994  else

10996  for(i_=iy1; i_<=iy2;i_++)
10997  {
10998  y[i_] = beta*y[i_];
10999  }
11000  }

11010  {
11011  v += a[i,i_]*x[i_+i1_];

11014  }
11015  }
11016  else

11018 
11019  //
11020  // y := alpha*A'*x + beta*y;
11021  //

11023  {

11063  public static double pythag2(double x,
11064  double y,
11065  alglib.xparams _params)
11066  {
11067  double result = 0;
11068  double w = 0;
11069  double xabs = 0;
11070  double yabs = 0;
11071  double z = 0;
11072 
11073  xabs = Math.Abs(x);
11074  yabs = Math.Abs(y);
11075  w = Math.Max(xabs, yabs);
11076  z = Math.Min(xabs, yabs);
11077  if( (double)(z)==(double)(0) )
11078  {
11079  result = w;
11080  }
11081  else
11082  {
11083  result = w*Math.Sqrt(1+math.sqr(z/w));
11084  }
11085  return result;

11089  public static void matrixmatrixmultiply(double[,] a,
11090  int ai1,
11091  int ai2,
11092  int aj1,
11093  int aj2,
11094  bool transa,
11095  double[,] b,
11096  int bi1,
11097  int bi2,
11098  int bj1,
11099  int bj2,
11100  bool transb,
11101  double alpha,
11102  ref double[,] c,
11103  int ci1,
11104  int ci2,
11105  int cj1,
11106  int cj2,
11107  double beta,
11108  ref double[] work,
11109  alglib.xparams _params)
11110  {
11111  int arows = 0;
11112  int acols = 0;
11113  int brows = 0;
11114  int bcols = 0;
11115  int crows = 0;
11116  int i = 0;
11117  int j = 0;
11118  int k = 0;
11119  int l = 0;
11120  int r = 0;
11121  double v = 0;
11122  int i_ = 0;
11123  int i1_ = 0;
11124 
11125 
11126  //
11127  // Setup
11128  //
11129  if( !transa )
11130  {
11131  arows = ai2-ai1+1;
11132  acols = aj2-aj1+1;
11133  }
11134  else
11135  {
11136  arows = aj2-aj1+1;
11137  acols = ai2-ai1+1;
11138  }
11139  if( !transb )
11140  {
11141  brows = bi2-bi1+1;
11142  bcols = bj2-bj1+1;
11143  }
11144  else
11145  {
11146  brows = bj2-bj1+1;
11147  bcols = bi2-bi1+1;
11148  }
11149  alglib.ap.assert(acols==brows, "MatrixMatrixMultiply: incorrect matrix sizes!");
11150  if( ((arows<=0 || acols<=0) || brows<=0) || bcols<=0 )
11151  {
11152  return;
11153  }
11154  crows = arows;
11155 
11156  //
11157  // Test WORK
11158  //
11159  i = Math.Max(arows, acols);
11160  i = Math.Max(brows, i);
11161  i = Math.Max(i, bcols);
11162  work[1] = 0;
11163  work[i] = 0;
11164 
11165  //
11166  // Prepare C
11167  //
11168  if( (double)(beta)==(double)(0) )
11169  {
11170  for(i=ci1; i<=ci2; i++)
11171  {
11172  for(j=cj1; j<=cj2; j++)
11173  {
11174  c[i,j] = 0;
11175  }
11176  }
11177  }
11178  else
11179  {
11180  for(i=ci1; i<=ci2; i++)
11181  {
11182  for(i_=cj1; i_<=cj2;i_++)
11183  {
11184  c[i,i_] = beta*c[i,i_];
11185  }
11186  }
11187  }
11188 
11189  //
11190  // A*B
11191  //
11192  if( !transa && !transb )
11193  {
11194  for(l=ai1; l<=ai2; l++)
11195  {
11196  for(r=bi1; r<=bi2; r++)
11197  {
11198  v = alpha*a[l,aj1+r-bi1];
11199  k = ci1+l-ai1;
11200  i1_ = (bj1) - (cj1);
11201  for(i_=cj1; i_<=cj2;i_++)
11202  {
11203  c[k,i_] = c[k,i_] + v*b[r,i_+i1_];
11204  }
11205  }
11206  }
11207  return;
11208  }
11209 
11210  //
11211  // A*B'
11212  //
11213  if( !transa && transb )
11214  {
11215  if( arows*acols<brows*bcols )
11216  {
11217  for(r=bi1; r<=bi2; r++)
11218  {
11219  for(l=ai1; l<=ai2; l++)
11220  {
11221  i1_ = (bj1)-(aj1);
11222  v = 0.0;
11223  for(i_=aj1; i_<=aj2;i_++)
11224  {
11225  v += a[l,i_]*b[r,i_+i1_];
11226  }
11227  c[ci1+l-ai1,cj1+r-bi1] = c[ci1+l-ai1,cj1+r-bi1]+alpha*v;
11228  }
11229  }
11230  return;
11231  }
11232  else
11233  {
11234  for(l=ai1; l<=ai2; l++)
11235  {
11236  for(r=bi1; r<=bi2; r++)
11237  {
11238  i1_ = (bj1)-(aj1);
11239  v = 0.0;
11240  for(i_=aj1; i_<=aj2;i_++)
11241  {
11242  v += a[l,i_]*b[r,i_+i1_];
11243  }
11244  c[ci1+l-ai1,cj1+r-bi1] = c[ci1+l-ai1,cj1+r-bi1]+alpha*v;
11245  }
11246  }
11247  return;
11248  }
11249  }
11250 
11251  //
11252  // A'*B
11253  //
11254  if( transa && !transb )
11255  {
11256  for(l=aj1; l<=aj2; l++)
11257  {
11258  for(r=bi1; r<=bi2; r++)
11259  {
11260  v = alpha*a[ai1+r-bi1,l];
11261  k = ci1+l-aj1;
11262  i1_ = (bj1) - (cj1);
11263  for(i_=cj1; i_<=cj2;i_++)
11264  {
11265  c[k,i_] = c[k,i_] + v*b[r,i_+i1_];
11266  }
11267  }
11268  }
11269  return;
11270  }
11271 
11272  //
11273  // A'*B'
11274  //
11275  if( transa && transb )
11276  {
11277  if( arows*acols<brows*bcols )
11278  {
11279  for(r=bi1; r<=bi2; r++)
11280  {
11281  k = cj1+r-bi1;
11282  for(i=1; i<=crows; i++)
11283  {
11284  work[i] = 0.0;
11285  }
11286  for(l=ai1; l<=ai2; l++)
11287  {
11288  v = alpha*b[r,bj1+l-ai1];
11289  i1_ = (aj1) - (1);
11290  for(i_=1; i_<=crows;i_++)
11291  {
11292  work[i_] = work[i_] + v*a[l,i_+i1_];
11293  }
11294  }
11295  i1_ = (1) - (ci1);
11296  for(i_=ci1; i_<=ci2;i_++)
11297  {
11298  c[i_,k] = c[i_,k] + work[i_+i1_];
11299  }
11300  }
11301  return;
11302  }
11303  else
11304  {
11305  for(l=aj1; l<=aj2; l++)
11306  {
11307  k = ai2-ai1+1;
11308  i1_ = (ai1) - (1);
11309  for(i_=1; i_<=k;i_++)
11310  {
11311  work[i_] = a[i_+i1_,l];
11312  }
11313  for(r=bi1; r<=bi2; r++)
11314  {
11315  i1_ = (bj1)-(1);
11316  v = 0.0;
11317  for(i_=1; i_<=k;i_++)
11318  {
11319  v += work[i_]*b[r,i_+i1_];
11320  }
11321  c[ci1+l-aj1,cj1+r-bi1] = c[ci1+l-aj1,cj1+r-bi1]+alpha*v;
11322  }
11323  }
11324  return;
11325  }
11326  }
11327  }

11373  _result.dg = dg;
11374  _result.dgm = dgm;
11375  _result.dginit = dginit;
11376  _result.dgtest = dgtest;
11377  _result.dgx = dgx;
11378  _result.dgxm = dgxm;
11379  _result.dgy = dgy;
11380  _result.dgym = dgym;
11381  _result.finit = finit;
11382  _result.ftest1 = ftest1;
11383  _result.fm = fm;
11384  _result.fx = fx;
11385  _result.fxm = fxm;
11386  _result.fy = fy;
11387  _result.fym = fym;
11388  _result.stx = stx;
11389  _result.sty = sty;
11390  _result.stmin = stmin;
11391  _result.stmax = stmax;
11392  _result.width = width;
11393  _result.width1 = width1;
11394  _result.xtrapf = xtrapf;
11395  return _result;
11396  }
11397  };
11398 
11399 
11400  public class armijostate : apobject
11401  {
11402  public bool needf;
11403  public double[] x;
11404  public double f;
11405  public int n;
11406  public double[] xbase;
11407  public double[] s;
11408  public double stplen;
11409  public double fcur;
11410  public double stpmax;
11411  public int fmax;
11412  public int nfev;
11413  public int info;
11414  public rcommstate rstate;
11415  public armijostate()
11416  {
11417  init();
11418  }
11419  public override void init()
11420  {
11421  x = new double[0];
11422  xbase = new double[0];
11423  s = new double[0];
11424  rstate = new rcommstate();
11425  }
11426  public override alglib.apobject make_copy()
11427  {
11428  armijostate _result = new armijostate();
11429  _result.needf = needf;
11430  _result.x = (double[])x.Clone();
11431  _result.f = f;
11432  _result.n = n;
11433  _result.xbase = (double[])xbase.Clone();
11434  _result.s = (double[])s.Clone();
11435  _result.stplen = stplen;
11436  _result.fcur = fcur;
11437  _result.stpmax = stpmax;
11438  _result.fmax = fmax;
11439  _result.nfev = nfev;
11440  _result.info = info;
11441  _result.rstate = (rcommstate)rstate.make_copy();
11442  return _result;
11443  }
11444  };
11445 
11446 
11447 
11448 
11449  public const double ftol = 0.001;
11450  public const double xtol = 100*math.machineepsilon;
11451  public const int maxfev = 20;
11452  public const double stpmin = 1.0E-50;
11453  public const double defstpmax = 1.0E+50;
11454  public const double armijofactor = 1.3;
11455 
11456 
11457  /*************************************************************************
11458  Normalizes direction/step pair: makes |D|=1, scales Stp.
11459  If |D|=0, it returns, leavind D/Stp unchanged.
11460 
11461  -- ALGLIB --
11462  Copyright 01.04.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
11463  *************************************************************************/
11464  public static void linminnormalized(ref double[] d,
11465  ref double stp,
11466  int n,
11467  alglib.xparams _params)
11468  {
11469  double mx = 0;
11470  double s = 0;
11471  int i = 0;
11472  int i_ = 0;
11473 
11474 
11475  //
11476  // first, scale D to avoid underflow/overflow durng squaring
11477  //
11478  mx = 0;
11479  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
11480  {
11481  mx = Math.Max(mx, Math.Abs(d[i]));
11482  }
11483  if( (double)(mx)==(double)(0) )
11484  {
11485  return;
11486  }
11487  s = 1/mx;
11488  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11489  {
11490  d[i_] = s*d[i_];
11491  }
11492  stp = stp/s;
11493 
11494  //
11495  // normalize D
11496  //
11497  s = 0.0;
11498  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11499  {
11500  s += d[i_]*d[i_];
11501  }
11502  s = 1/Math.Sqrt(s);
11503  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11504  {
11505  d[i_] = s*d[i_];
11506  }
11507  stp = stp/s;
11508  }
11509 
11510 
11511  /*************************************************************************
11512  THE PURPOSE OF MCSRCH IS TO FIND A STEP WHICH SATISFIES A SUFFICIENT
11513  DECREASE CONDITION AND A CURVATURE CONDITION.
11514 
11515  AT EACH STAGE THE SUBROUTINE UPDATES AN INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY WITH
11516  ENDPOINTS STX AND STY. THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY IS INITIALLY CHOSEN
11517  SO THAT IT CONTAINS A MINIMIZER OF THE MODIFIED FUNCTION
11518 
11519  F(X+STP*S) - F(X) - FTOL*STP*(GRADF(X)'S).
11520 
11521  IF A STEP IS OBTAINED FOR WHICH THE MODIFIED FUNCTION HAS A NONPOSITIVE
11522  FUNCTION VALUE AND NONNEGATIVE DERIVATIVE, THEN THE INTERVAL OF
11523  UNCERTAINTY IS CHOSEN SO THAT IT CONTAINS A MINIMIZER OF F(X+STP*S).
11524 
11525  THE ALGORITHM IS DESIGNED TO FIND A STEP WHICH SATISFIES THE SUFFICIENT
11526  DECREASE CONDITION
11527 
11528  F(X+STP*S) .LE. F(X) + FTOL*STP*(GRADF(X)'S),
11529 
11530  AND THE CURVATURE CONDITION
11531 
11532  ABS(GRADF(X+STP*S)'S)) .LE. GTOL*ABS(GRADF(X)'S).
11533 
11534  IF FTOL IS LESS THAN GTOL AND IF, FOR EXAMPLE, THE FUNCTION IS BOUNDED
11535  BELOW, THEN THERE IS ALWAYS A STEP WHICH SATISFIES BOTH CONDITIONS.
11536  IF NO STEP CAN BE FOUND WHICH SATISFIES BOTH CONDITIONS, THEN THE
11537  ALGORITHM USUALLY STOPS WHEN ROUNDING ERRORS PREVENT FURTHER PROGRESS.
11538  IN THIS CASE STP ONLY SATISFIES THE SUFFICIENT DECREASE CONDITION.
11539 
11540 
11541  :::::::::::::IMPORTANT NOTES:::::::::::::
11542 
11543  NOTE 1:
11544 
11545  This routine guarantees that it will stop at the last point where function
11546  value was calculated. It won't make several additional function evaluations
11547  after finding good point. So if you store function evaluations requested by
11548  this routine, you can be sure that last one is the point where we've stopped.
11549 
11550  NOTE 2:
11551 
11552  when 0<StpMax<StpMin, algorithm will terminate with INFO=5 and Stp=StpMax
11553 
11554  NOTE 3:
11555 
11556  this algorithm guarantees that, if MCINFO=1 or MCINFO=5, then:
11557  * F(final_point)<F(initial_point) - strict inequality
11558  * final_point<>initial_point - after rounding to machine precision
11559 
11560  NOTE 4:
11561 
11562  when non-descent direction is specified, algorithm stops with MCINFO=0,
11563  Stp=0 and initial point at X[].
11564  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
11565 
11566 
11567  PARAMETERS DESCRIPRION
11568 
11569  STAGE IS ZERO ON FIRST CALL, ZERO ON FINAL EXIT
11570 
11571  N IS A POSITIVE INTEGER INPUT VARIABLE SET TO THE NUMBER OF VARIABLES.
11572 
11573  X IS AN ARRAY OF LENGTH N. ON INPUT IT MUST CONTAIN THE BASE POINT FOR
11574  THE LINE SEARCH. ON OUTPUT IT CONTAINS X+STP*S.
11575 
11576  F IS A VARIABLE. ON INPUT IT MUST CONTAIN THE VALUE OF F AT X. ON OUTPUT
11577  IT CONTAINS THE VALUE OF F AT X + STP*S.
11578 
11579  G IS AN ARRAY OF LENGTH N. ON INPUT IT MUST CONTAIN THE GRADIENT OF F AT X.
11580  ON OUTPUT IT CONTAINS THE GRADIENT OF F AT X + STP*S.
11581 
11582  S IS AN INPUT ARRAY OF LENGTH N WHICH SPECIFIES THE SEARCH DIRECTION.
11583 
11584  STP IS A NONNEGATIVE VARIABLE. ON INPUT STP CONTAINS AN INITIAL ESTIMATE
11585  OF A SATISFACTORY STEP. ON OUTPUT STP CONTAINS THE FINAL ESTIMATE.
11586 
11587  FTOL AND GTOL ARE NONNEGATIVE INPUT VARIABLES. TERMINATION OCCURS WHEN THE
11588  SUFFICIENT DECREASE CONDITION AND THE DIRECTIONAL DERIVATIVE CONDITION ARE
11589  SATISFIED.
11590 
11591  XTOL IS A NONNEGATIVE INPUT VARIABLE. TERMINATION OCCURS WHEN THE RELATIVE
11592  WIDTH OF THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY IS AT MOST XTOL.
11593 
11594  STPMIN AND STPMAX ARE NONNEGATIVE INPUT VARIABLES WHICH SPECIFY LOWER AND
11595  UPPER BOUNDS FOR THE STEP.
11596 
11597  MAXFEV IS A POSITIVE INTEGER INPUT VARIABLE. TERMINATION OCCURS WHEN THE
11598  NUMBER OF CALLS TO FCN IS AT LEAST MAXFEV BY THE END OF AN ITERATION.
11599 
11600  INFO IS AN INTEGER OUTPUT VARIABLE SET AS FOLLOWS:
11601  INFO = 0 IMPROPER INPUT PARAMETERS.
11602 
11603  INFO = 1 THE SUFFICIENT DECREASE CONDITION AND THE
11604  DIRECTIONAL DERIVATIVE CONDITION HOLD.
11605 
11606  INFO = 2 RELATIVE WIDTH OF THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY
11607  IS AT MOST XTOL.
11608 
11609  INFO = 3 NUMBER OF CALLS TO FCN HAS REACHED MAXFEV.
11610 
11611  INFO = 4 THE STEP IS AT THE LOWER BOUND STPMIN.
11612 
11613  INFO = 5 THE STEP IS AT THE UPPER BOUND STPMAX.
11614 
11615  INFO = 6 ROUNDING ERRORS PREVENT FURTHER PROGRESS.
11616  THERE MAY NOT BE A STEP WHICH SATISFIES THE
11617  SUFFICIENT DECREASE AND CURVATURE CONDITIONS.
11618  TOLERANCES MAY BE TOO SMALL.
11619 
11620  NFEV IS AN INTEGER OUTPUT VARIABLE SET TO THE NUMBER OF CALLS TO FCN.
11621 
11622  WA IS A WORK ARRAY OF LENGTH N.
11623 
11624  ARGONNE NATIONAL LABORATORY. MINPACK PROJECT. JUNE 1983
11625  JORGE J. MORE', DAVID J. THUENTE
11626  *************************************************************************/
11627  public static void mcsrch(int n,
11628  ref double[] x,
11629  ref double f,
11630  ref double[] g,
11631  double[] s,
11632  ref double stp,
11633  double stpmax,
11634  double gtol,
11635  ref int info,
11636  ref int nfev,
11637  ref double[] wa,
11638  linminstate state,
11639  ref int stage,
11640  alglib.xparams _params)
11641  {
11642  int i = 0;
11643  double v = 0;
11644  double p5 = 0;
11645  double p66 = 0;
11646  double zero = 0;
11647  int i_ = 0;
11648 
11649 
11650  //
11651  // init
11652  //
11653  p5 = 0.5;
11654  p66 = 0.66;
11655  state.xtrapf = 4.0;
11656  zero = 0;
11657  if( (double)(stpmax)==(double)(0) )
11658  {
11659  stpmax = defstpmax;
11660  }
11661  if( (double)(stp)<(double)(stpmin) )
11662  {
11663  stp = stpmin;
11664  }
11665  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(stpmax) )
11666  {
11667  stp = stpmax;
11668  }
11669 
11670  //
11671  // Main cycle
11672  //
11673  while( true )
11674  {
11675  if( stage==0 )
11676  {
11677 
11678  //
11679  // NEXT
11680  //
11681  stage = 2;
11682  continue;
11683  }
11684  if( stage==2 )
11685  {
11686  state.infoc = 1;
11687  info = 0;
11688 
11689  //
11690  // CHECK THE INPUT PARAMETERS FOR ERRORS.
11691  //
11692  if( (double)(stpmax)<(double)(stpmin) && (double)(stpmax)>(double)(0) )
11693  {
11694  info = 5;
11695  stp = stpmax;
11696  stage = 0;
11697  return;
11698  }
11699  if( ((((((n<=0 || (double)(stp)<=(double)(0)) || (double)(ftol)<(double)(0)) || (double)(gtol)<(double)(zero)) || (double)(xtol)<(double)(zero)) || (double)(stpmin)<(double)(zero)) || (double)(stpmax)<(double)(stpmin)) || maxfev<=0 )
11700  {
11701  stage = 0;
11702  return;
11703  }
11704 
11705  //
11706  // COMPUTE THE INITIAL GRADIENT IN THE SEARCH DIRECTION
11707  // AND CHECK THAT S IS A DESCENT DIRECTION.
11708  //
11709  v = 0.0;
11710  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11711  {
11712  v += g[i_]*s[i_];
11713  }
11714  state.dginit = v;
11715  if( (double)(state.dginit)>=(double)(0) )
11716  {
11717  stage = 0;
11718  stp = 0;
11719  return;
11720  }
11721 
11722  //
11723  // INITIALIZE LOCAL VARIABLES.
11724  //
11725  state.brackt = false;
11726  state.stage1 = true;
11727  nfev = 0;
11728  state.finit = f;
11729  state.dgtest = ftol*state.dginit;
11730  state.width = stpmax-stpmin;
11731  state.width1 = state.width/p5;
11732  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11733  {
11734  wa[i_] = x[i_];
11735  }
11736 
11737  //
11738  // THE VARIABLES STX, FX, DGX CONTAIN THE VALUES OF THE STEP,
11739  // FUNCTION, AND DIRECTIONAL DERIVATIVE AT THE BEST STEP.
11740  // THE VARIABLES STY, FY, DGY CONTAIN THE VALUE OF THE STEP,
11741  // FUNCTION, AND DERIVATIVE AT THE OTHER ENDPOINT OF
11742  // THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY.
11743  // THE VARIABLES STP, F, DG CONTAIN THE VALUES OF THE STEP,
11744  // FUNCTION, AND DERIVATIVE AT THE CURRENT STEP.
11745  //
11746  state.stx = 0;
11747  state.fx = state.finit;
11748  state.dgx = state.dginit;
11749  state.sty = 0;
11750  state.fy = state.finit;
11751  state.dgy = state.dginit;
11752 
11753  //
11754  // NEXT
11755  //
11756  stage = 3;
11757  continue;
11758  }
11759  if( stage==3 )
11760  {
11761 
11762  //
11763  // START OF ITERATION.
11764  //
11765  // SET THE MINIMUM AND MAXIMUM STEPS TO CORRESPOND
11766  // TO THE PRESENT INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY.
11767  //
11768  if( state.brackt )
11769  {
11770  if( (double)(state.stx)<(double)(state.sty) )
11771  {
11772  state.stmin = state.stx;
11773  state.stmax = state.sty;
11774  }
11775  else
11776  {
11777  state.stmin = state.sty;
11778  state.stmax = state.stx;
11779  }
11780  }
11781  else
11782  {
11783  state.stmin = state.stx;
11784  state.stmax = stp+state.xtrapf*(stp-state.stx);
11785  }
11786 
11787  //
11788  // FORCE THE STEP TO BE WITHIN THE BOUNDS STPMAX AND STPMIN.
11789  //
11790  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(stpmax) )
11791  {
11792  stp = stpmax;
11793  }
11794  if( (double)(stp)<(double)(stpmin) )
11795  {
11796  stp = stpmin;
11797  }
11798 
11799  //
11800  // IF AN UNUSUAL TERMINATION IS TO OCCUR THEN LET
11801  // STP BE THE LOWEST POINT OBTAINED SO FAR.
11802  //
11803  if( (((state.brackt && ((double)(stp)<=(double)(state.stmin) || (double)(stp)>=(double)(state.stmax))) || nfev>=maxfev-1) || state.infoc==0) || (state.brackt && (double)(state.stmax-state.stmin)<=(double)(xtol*state.stmax)) )
11804  {
11805  stp = state.stx;
11806  }
11807 
11808  //
11809  // EVALUATE THE FUNCTION AND GRADIENT AT STP
11810  // AND COMPUTE THE DIRECTIONAL DERIVATIVE.
11811  //
11812  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11813  {
11814  x[i_] = wa[i_];
11815  }
11816  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11817  {
11818  x[i_] = x[i_] + stp*s[i_];
11819  }
11820 
11821  //
11822  // NEXT
11823  //
11824  stage = 4;
11825  return;
11826  }
11827  if( stage==4 )
11828  {
11829  info = 0;
11830  nfev = nfev+1;
11831  v = 0.0;
11832  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
11833  {
11834  v += g[i_]*s[i_];
11835  }
11836  state.dg = v;
11837  state.ftest1 = state.finit+stp*state.dgtest;
11838 
11839  //
11840  // TEST FOR CONVERGENCE.
11841  //
11842  if( (state.brackt && ((double)(stp)<=(double)(state.stmin) || (double)(stp)>=(double)(state.stmax))) || state.infoc==0 )
11843  {
11844  info = 6;
11845  }
11846  if( (((double)(stp)==(double)(stpmax) && (double)(f)<(double)(state.finit)) && (double)(f)<=(double)(state.ftest1)) && (double)(state.dg)<=(double)(state.dgtest) )
11847  {
11848  info = 5;
11849  }
11850  if( (double)(stp)==(double)(stpmin) && (((double)(f)>=(double)(state.finit) || (double)(f)>(double)(state.ftest1)) || (double)(state.dg)>=(double)(state.dgtest)) )
11851  {
11852  info = 4;
11853  }
11854  if( nfev>=maxfev )
11855  {
11856  info = 3;
11857  }
11858  if( state.brackt && (double)(state.stmax-state.stmin)<=(double)(xtol*state.stmax) )
11859  {
11860  info = 2;
11861  }
11862  if( ((double)(f)<(double)(state.finit) && (double)(f)<=(double)(state.ftest1)) && (double)(Math.Abs(state.dg))<=(double)(-(gtol*state.dginit)) )
11863  {
11864  info = 1;
11865  }
11866 
11867  //
11868  // CHECK FOR TERMINATION.
11869  //
11870  if( info!=0 )
11871  {
11872 
11873  //
11874  // Check guarantees provided by the function for INFO=1 or INFO=5
11875  //
11876  if( info==1 || info==5 )
11877  {
11878  v = 0.0;
11879  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
11880  {
11881  v = v+(wa[i]-x[i])*(wa[i]-x[i]);
11882  }
11883  if( (double)(f)>=(double)(state.finit) || (double)(v)==(double)(0.0) )
11884  {
11885  info = 6;
11886  }
11887  }
11888  stage = 0;
11889  return;
11890  }
11891 
11892  //
11893  // IN THE FIRST STAGE WE SEEK A STEP FOR WHICH THE MODIFIED
11894  // FUNCTION HAS A NONPOSITIVE VALUE AND NONNEGATIVE DERIVATIVE.
11895  //
11896  if( (state.stage1 && (double)(f)<=(double)(state.ftest1)) && (double)(state.dg)>=(double)(Math.Min(ftol, gtol)*state.dginit) )
11897  {
11898  state.stage1 = false;
11899  }
11900 
11901  //
11902  // A MODIFIED FUNCTION IS USED TO PREDICT THE STEP ONLY IF
11903  // WE HAVE NOT OBTAINED A STEP FOR WHICH THE MODIFIED
11904  // FUNCTION HAS A NONPOSITIVE FUNCTION VALUE AND NONNEGATIVE
11905  // DERIVATIVE, AND IF A LOWER FUNCTION VALUE HAS BEEN
11906  // OBTAINED BUT THE DECREASE IS NOT SUFFICIENT.
11907  //
11908  if( (state.stage1 && (double)(f)<=(double)(state.fx)) && (double)(f)>(double)(state.ftest1) )
11909  {
11910 
11911  //
11912  // DEFINE THE MODIFIED FUNCTION AND DERIVATIVE VALUES.
11913  //
11914  state.fm = f-stp*state.dgtest;
11915  state.fxm = state.fx-state.stx*state.dgtest;
11916  state.fym = state.fy-state.sty*state.dgtest;
11917  state.dgm = state.dg-state.dgtest;
11918  state.dgxm = state.dgx-state.dgtest;
11919  state.dgym = state.dgy-state.dgtest;
11920 
11921  //
11922  // CALL CSTEP TO UPDATE THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY
11923  // AND TO COMPUTE THE NEW STEP.
11924  //
11925  mcstep(ref state.stx, ref state.fxm, ref state.dgxm, ref state.sty, ref state.fym, ref state.dgym, ref stp, state.fm, state.dgm, ref state.brackt, state.stmin, state.stmax, ref state.infoc, _params);
11926 
11927  //
11928  // RESET THE FUNCTION AND GRADIENT VALUES FOR F.
11929  //
11930  state.fx = state.fxm+state.stx*state.dgtest;
11931  state.fy = state.fym+state.sty*state.dgtest;
11932  state.dgx = state.dgxm+state.dgtest;
11933  state.dgy = state.dgym+state.dgtest;
11934  }
11935  else
11936  {
11937 
11938  //
11939  // CALL MCSTEP TO UPDATE THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY
11940  // AND TO COMPUTE THE NEW STEP.
11941  //
11942  mcstep(ref state.stx, ref state.fx, ref state.dgx, ref state.sty, ref state.fy, ref state.dgy, ref stp, f, state.dg, ref state.brackt, state.stmin, state.stmax, ref state.infoc, _params);
11943  }
11944 
11945  //
11946  // FORCE A SUFFICIENT DECREASE IN THE SIZE OF THE
11947  // INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY.
11948  //
11949  if( state.brackt )
11950  {
11951  if( (double)(Math.Abs(state.sty-state.stx))>=(double)(p66*state.width1) )
11952  {
11953  stp = state.stx+p5*(state.sty-state.stx);
11954  }
11955  state.width1 = state.width;
11956  state.width = Math.Abs(state.sty-state.stx);
11957  }
11958 
11959  //
11960  // NEXT.
11961  //
11962  stage = 3;
11963  continue;
11964  }
11965  }
11966  }
11967 
11968 
11969  /*************************************************************************
11970  These functions perform Armijo line search using at most FMAX function
11971  evaluations. It doesn't enforce some kind of " sufficient decrease"
11972  criterion - it just tries different Armijo steps and returns optimum found
11973  so far.
11974 
11975  Optimization is done using F-rcomm interface:
11976  * ArmijoCreate initializes State structure
11977  (reusing previously allocated buffers)
11978  * ArmijoIteration is subsequently called
11979  * ArmijoResults returns results
11980 
11981  INPUT PARAMETERS:
11982  N - problem size
11983  X - array[N], starting point
11984  F - F(X+S*STP)
11985  S - step direction, S>0
11986  STP - step length
11987  STPMAX - maximum value for STP or zero (if no limit is imposed)
11988  FMAX - maximum number of function evaluations
11989  State - optimization state
11990 
11991  -- ALGLIB --
11992  Copyright 05.10.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
11993  *************************************************************************/
11994  public static void armijocreate(int n,
11995  double[] x,
11996  double f,
11997  double[] s,
11998  double stp,
11999  double stpmax,
12000  int fmax,
12001  armijostate state,
12002  alglib.xparams _params)
12003  {
12004  int i_ = 0;
12005 
12006  if( alglib.ap.len(state.x)<n )
12007  {
12008  state.x = new double[n];
12009  }
12010  if( alglib.ap.len(state.xbase)<n )
12011  {
12012  state.xbase = new double[n];
12013  }
12014  if( alglib.ap.len(state.s)<n )
12015  {
12016  state.s = new double[n];
12017  }
12018  state.stpmax = stpmax;
12019  state.fmax = fmax;
12020  state.stplen = stp;
12021  state.fcur = f;
12022  state.n = n;
12023  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12024  {
12025  state.xbase[i_] = x[i_];
12026  }
12027  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12028  {
12029  state.s[i_] = s[i_];
12030  }
12031  state.rstate.ia = new int[0+1];
12032  state.rstate.ra = new double[0+1];
12033  state.rstate.stage = -1;
12034  }
12035 
12036 
12037  /*************************************************************************
12038  This is rcomm-based search function
12039 
12040  -- ALGLIB --
12041  Copyright 05.10.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
12042  *************************************************************************/
12043  public static bool armijoiteration(armijostate state,
12044  alglib.xparams _params)
12045  {
12046  bool result = new bool();
12047  double v = 0;
12048  int n = 0;
12049  int i_ = 0;
12050 
12051 
12052  //
12053  // Reverse communication preparations
12054  // I know it looks ugly, but it works the same way
12055  // anywhere from C++ to Python.
12056  //
12057  // This code initializes locals by:
12058  // * random values determined during code
12059  // generation - on first subroutine call
12060  // * values from previous call - on subsequent calls
12061  //
12062  if( state.rstate.stage>=0 )
12063  {
12064  n = state.rstate.ia[0];
12065  v = state.rstate.ra[0];
12066  }
12067  else
12068  {
12069  n = 359;
12070  v = -58;
12071  }
12072  if( state.rstate.stage==0 )
12073  {
12074  goto lbl_0;
12075  }
12076  if( state.rstate.stage==1 )
12077  {
12078  goto lbl_1;
12079  }
12080  if( state.rstate.stage==2 )
12081  {
12082  goto lbl_2;
12083  }
12084  if( state.rstate.stage==3 )
12085  {
12086  goto lbl_3;
12087  }
12088 
12089  //
12090  // Routine body
12091  //
12092  if( ((double)(state.stplen)<=(double)(0) || (double)(state.stpmax)<(double)(0)) || state.fmax<2 )
12093  {
12094  state.info = 0;
12095  result = false;
12096  return result;
12097  }
12098  if( (double)(state.stplen)<=(double)(stpmin) )
12099  {
12100  state.info = 4;
12101  result = false;
12102  return result;
12103  }
12104  n = state.n;
12105  state.nfev = 0;
12106 
12107  //
12108  // We always need F
12109  //
12110  state.needf = true;
12111 
12112  //
12113  // Bound StpLen
12114  //
12115  if( (double)(state.stplen)>(double)(state.stpmax) && (double)(state.stpmax)!=(double)(0) )
12116  {
12117  state.stplen = state.stpmax;
12118  }
12119 
12120  //
12121  // Increase length
12122  //
12123  v = state.stplen*armijofactor;
12124  if( (double)(v)>(double)(state.stpmax) && (double)(state.stpmax)!=(double)(0) )
12125  {
12126  v = state.stpmax;
12127  }
12128  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12129  {
12130  state.x[i_] = state.xbase[i_];
12131  }
12132  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12133  {
12134  state.x[i_] = state.x[i_] + v*state.s[i_];
12135  }
12136  state.rstate.stage = 0;
12137  goto lbl_rcomm;
12138  lbl_0:
12139  state.nfev = state.nfev+1;
12140  if( (double)(state.f)>=(double)(state.fcur) )
12141  {
12142  goto lbl_4;
12143  }
12144  state.stplen = v;
12145  state.fcur = state.f;
12146  lbl_6:
12147  if( false )
12148  {
12149  goto lbl_7;
12150  }
12151 
12152  //
12153  // test stopping conditions
12154  //
12155  if( state.nfev>=state.fmax )
12156  {
12157  state.info = 3;
12158  result = false;
12159  return result;
12160  }
12161  if( (double)(state.stplen)>=(double)(state.stpmax) )
12162  {
12163  state.info = 5;
12164  result = false;
12165  return result;
12166  }
12167 
12168  //
12169  // evaluate F
12170  //
12171  v = state.stplen*armijofactor;
12172  if( (double)(v)>(double)(state.stpmax) && (double)(state.stpmax)!=(double)(0) )
12173  {
12174  v = state.stpmax;
12175  }
12176  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12177  {
12178  state.x[i_] = state.xbase[i_];
12179  }
12180  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12181  {
12182  state.x[i_] = state.x[i_] + v*state.s[i_];
12183  }
12184  state.rstate.stage = 1;
12185  goto lbl_rcomm;
12186  lbl_1:
12187  state.nfev = state.nfev+1;
12188 
12189  //
12190  // make decision
12191  //
12192  if( (double)(state.f)<(double)(state.fcur) )
12193  {
12194  state.stplen = v;
12195  state.fcur = state.f;
12196  }
12197  else
12198  {
12199  state.info = 1;
12200  result = false;
12201  return result;
12202  }
12203  goto lbl_6;
12204  lbl_7:
12205  lbl_4:
12206 
12207  //
12208  // Decrease length
12209  //
12210  v = state.stplen/armijofactor;
12211  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12212  {
12213  state.x[i_] = state.xbase[i_];
12214  }
12215  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12216  {
12217  state.x[i_] = state.x[i_] + v*state.s[i_];
12218  }
12219  state.rstate.stage = 2;
12220  goto lbl_rcomm;
12221  lbl_2:
12222  state.nfev = state.nfev+1;
12223  if( (double)(state.f)>=(double)(state.fcur) )
12224  {
12225  goto lbl_8;
12226  }
12227  state.stplen = state.stplen/armijofactor;
12228  state.fcur = state.f;
12229  lbl_10:
12230  if( false )
12231  {
12232  goto lbl_11;
12233  }
12234 
12235  //
12236  // test stopping conditions
12237  //
12238  if( state.nfev>=state.fmax )
12239  {
12240  state.info = 3;
12241  result = false;
12242  return result;
12243  }
12244  if( (double)(state.stplen)<=(double)(stpmin) )
12245  {
12246  state.info = 4;
12247  result = false;
12248  return result;
12249  }
12250 
12251  //
12252  // evaluate F
12253  //
12254  v = state.stplen/armijofactor;
12255  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12256  {
12257  state.x[i_] = state.xbase[i_];
12258  }
12259  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12260  {
12261  state.x[i_] = state.x[i_] + v*state.s[i_];
12262  }
12263  state.rstate.stage = 3;
12264  goto lbl_rcomm;
12265  lbl_3:
12266  state.nfev = state.nfev+1;
12267 
12268  //
12269  // make decision
12270  //
12271  if( (double)(state.f)<(double)(state.fcur) )
12272  {
12273  state.stplen = state.stplen/armijofactor;
12274  state.fcur = state.f;
12275  }
12276  else
12277  {
12278  state.info = 1;
12279  result = false;
12280  return result;
12281  }
12282  goto lbl_10;
12283  lbl_11:
12284  lbl_8:
12285 
12286  //
12287  // Nothing to be done
12288  //
12289  state.info = 1;
12290  result = false;
12291  return result;
12292 
12293  //
12294  // Saving state
12295  //
12296  lbl_rcomm:
12297  result = true;
12298  state.rstate.ia[0] = n;
12299  state.rstate.ra[0] = v;
12300  return result;
12301  }
12302 
12303 
12304  /*************************************************************************
12305  Results of Armijo search
12306 
12307  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
12308  INFO - on output it is set to one of the return codes:
12309  * 0 improper input params
12310  * 1 optimum step is found with at most FMAX evaluations
12311  * 3 FMAX evaluations were used,
12312  X contains optimum found so far
12313  * 4 step is at lower bound STPMIN
12314  * 5 step is at upper bound
12315  STP - step length (in case of failure it is still returned)
12316  F - function value (in case of failure it is still returned)
12317 
12318  -- ALGLIB --
12319  Copyright 05.10.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
12320  *************************************************************************/
12321  public static void armijoresults(armijostate state,
12322  ref int info,
12323  ref double stp,
12324  ref double f,
12325  alglib.xparams _params)
12326  {
12327  info = state.info;
12328  stp = state.stplen;
12329  f = state.fcur;
12330  }
12331 
12332 
12333  private static void mcstep(ref double stx,
12334  ref double fx,
12335  ref double dx,
12336  ref double sty,
12337  ref double fy,
12338  ref double dy,
12339  ref double stp,
12340  double fp,
12341  double dp,
12342  ref bool brackt,
12343  double stmin,
12344  double stmax,
12345  ref int info,
12346  alglib.xparams _params)
12347  {
12348  bool bound = new bool();
12349  double gamma = 0;
12350  double p = 0;
12351  double q = 0;
12352  double r = 0;
12353  double s = 0;
12354  double sgnd = 0;
12355  double stpc = 0;
12356  double stpf = 0;
12357  double stpq = 0;
12358  double theta = 0;
12359 
12360  info = 0;
12361 
12362  //
12363  // CHECK THE INPUT PARAMETERS FOR ERRORS.
12364  //
12365  if( ((brackt && ((double)(stp)<=(double)(Math.Min(stx, sty)) || (double)(stp)>=(double)(Math.Max(stx, sty)))) || (double)(dx*(stp-stx))>=(double)(0)) || (double)(stmax)<(double)(stmin) )
12366  {
12367  return;
12368  }
12369 
12370  //
12371  // DETERMINE IF THE DERIVATIVES HAVE OPPOSITE SIGN.
12372  //
12373  sgnd = dp*(dx/Math.Abs(dx));
12374 
12375  //
12376  // FIRST CASE. A HIGHER FUNCTION VALUE.
12377  // THE MINIMUM IS BRACKETED. IF THE CUBIC STEP IS CLOSER
12378  // TO STX THAN THE QUADRATIC STEP, THE CUBIC STEP IS TAKEN,
12379  // ELSE THE AVERAGE OF THE CUBIC AND QUADRATIC STEPS IS TAKEN.
12380  //
12381  if( (double)(fp)>(double)(fx) )
12382  {
12383  info = 1;
12384  bound = true;
12385  theta = 3*(fx-fp)/(stp-stx)+dx+dp;
12386  s = Math.Max(Math.Abs(theta), Math.Max(Math.Abs(dx), Math.Abs(dp)));
12387  gamma = s*Math.Sqrt(math.sqr(theta/s)-dx/s*(dp/s));
12388  if( (double)(stp)<(double)(stx) )
12389  {
12390  gamma = -gamma;
12391  }
12392  p = gamma-dx+theta;
12393  q = gamma-dx+gamma+dp;
12394  r = p/q;
12395  stpc = stx+r*(stp-stx);
12396  stpq = stx+dx/((fx-fp)/(stp-stx)+dx)/2*(stp-stx);
12397  if( (double)(Math.Abs(stpc-stx))<(double)(Math.Abs(stpq-stx)) )
12398  {
12399  stpf = stpc;
12400  }
12401  else
12402  {
12403  stpf = stpc+(stpq-stpc)/2;
12404  }
12405  brackt = true;
12406  }
12407  else
12408  {
12409  if( (double)(sgnd)<(double)(0) )
12410  {
12411 
12412  //
12413  // SECOND CASE. A LOWER FUNCTION VALUE AND DERIVATIVES OF
12414  // OPPOSITE SIGN. THE MINIMUM IS BRACKETED. IF THE CUBIC
12415  // STEP IS CLOSER TO STX THAN THE QUADRATIC (SECANT) STEP,
12416  // THE CUBIC STEP IS TAKEN, ELSE THE QUADRATIC STEP IS TAKEN.
12417  //
12418  info = 2;
12419  bound = false;
12420  theta = 3*(fx-fp)/(stp-stx)+dx+dp;
12421  s = Math.Max(Math.Abs(theta), Math.Max(Math.Abs(dx), Math.Abs(dp)));
12422  gamma = s*Math.Sqrt(math.sqr(theta/s)-dx/s*(dp/s));
12423  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(stx) )
12424  {
12425  gamma = -gamma;
12426  }
12427  p = gamma-dp+theta;
12428  q = gamma-dp+gamma+dx;
12429  r = p/q;
12430  stpc = stp+r*(stx-stp);
12431  stpq = stp+dp/(dp-dx)*(stx-stp);
12432  if( (double)(Math.Abs(stpc-stp))>(double)(Math.Abs(stpq-stp)) )
12433  {
12434  stpf = stpc;
12435  }
12436  else
12437  {
12438  stpf = stpq;
12439  }
12440  brackt = true;
12441  }
12442  else
12443  {
12444  if( (double)(Math.Abs(dp))<(double)(Math.Abs(dx)) )
12445  {
12446 
12447  //
12448  // THIRD CASE. A LOWER FUNCTION VALUE, DERIVATIVES OF THE
12449  // SAME SIGN, AND THE MAGNITUDE OF THE DERIVATIVE DECREASES.
12450  // THE CUBIC STEP IS ONLY USED IF THE CUBIC TENDS TO INFINITY
12451  // IN THE DIRECTION OF THE STEP OR IF THE MINIMUM OF THE CUBIC
12452  // IS BEYOND STP. OTHERWISE THE CUBIC STEP IS DEFINED TO BE
12453  // EITHER STPMIN OR STPMAX. THE QUADRATIC (SECANT) STEP IS ALSO
12454  // COMPUTED AND IF THE MINIMUM IS BRACKETED THEN THE THE STEP
12455  // CLOSEST TO STX IS TAKEN, ELSE THE STEP FARTHEST AWAY IS TAKEN.
12456  //
12457  info = 3;
12458  bound = true;
12459  theta = 3*(fx-fp)/(stp-stx)+dx+dp;
12460  s = Math.Max(Math.Abs(theta), Math.Max(Math.Abs(dx), Math.Abs(dp)));
12461 
12462  //
12463  // THE CASE GAMMA = 0 ONLY ARISES IF THE CUBIC DOES NOT TEND
12464  // TO INFINITY IN THE DIRECTION OF THE STEP.
12465  //
12466  gamma = s*Math.Sqrt(Math.Max(0, math.sqr(theta/s)-dx/s*(dp/s)));
12467  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(stx) )
12468  {
12469  gamma = -gamma;
12470  }
12471  p = gamma-dp+theta;
12472  q = gamma+(dx-dp)+gamma;
12473  r = p/q;
12474  if( (double)(r)<(double)(0) && (double)(gamma)!=(double)(0) )
12475  {
12476  stpc = stp+r*(stx-stp);
12477  }
12478  else
12479  {
12480  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(stx) )
12481  {
12482  stpc = stmax;
12483  }
12484  else
12485  {
12486  stpc = stmin;
12487  }
12488  }
12489  stpq = stp+dp/(dp-dx)*(stx-stp);
12490  if( brackt )
12491  {
12492  if( (double)(Math.Abs(stp-stpc))<(double)(Math.Abs(stp-stpq)) )
12493  {
12494  stpf = stpc;
12495  }
12496  else
12497  {
12498  stpf = stpq;
12499  }
12500  }
12501  else
12502  {
12503  if( (double)(Math.Abs(stp-stpc))>(double)(Math.Abs(stp-stpq)) )
12504  {
12505  stpf = stpc;
12506  }
12507  else
12508  {
12509  stpf = stpq;
12510  }
12511  }
12512  }
12513  else
12514  {
12515 
12516  //
12517  // FOURTH CASE. A LOWER FUNCTION VALUE, DERIVATIVES OF THE
12518  // SAME SIGN, AND THE MAGNITUDE OF THE DERIVATIVE DOES
12519  // NOT DECREASE. IF THE MINIMUM IS NOT BRACKETED, THE STEP
12520  // IS EITHER STPMIN OR STPMAX, ELSE THE CUBIC STEP IS TAKEN.
12521  //
12522  info = 4;
12523  bound = false;
12524  if( brackt )
12525  {
12526  theta = 3*(fp-fy)/(sty-stp)+dy+dp;
12527  s = Math.Max(Math.Abs(theta), Math.Max(Math.Abs(dy), Math.Abs(dp)));
12528  gamma = s*Math.Sqrt(math.sqr(theta/s)-dy/s*(dp/s));
12529  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(sty) )
12530  {
12531  gamma = -gamma;
12532  }
12533  p = gamma-dp+theta;
12534  q = gamma-dp+gamma+dy;
12535  r = p/q;
12536  stpc = stp+r*(sty-stp);
12537  stpf = stpc;
12538  }
12539  else
12540  {
12541  if( (double)(stp)>(double)(stx) )
12542  {
12543  stpf = stmax;
12544  }
12545  else
12546  {
12547  stpf = stmin;
12548  }
12549  }
12550  }
12551  }
12552  }
12553 
12554  //
12555  // UPDATE THE INTERVAL OF UNCERTAINTY. THIS UPDATE DOES NOT
12556  // DEPEND ON THE NEW STEP OR THE CASE ANALYSIS ABOVE.
12557  //
12558  if( (double)(fp)>(double)(fx) )
12559  {
12560  sty = stp;
12561  fy = fp;
12562  dy = dp;
12563  }
12564  else
12565  {
12566  if( (double)(sgnd)<(double)(0.0) )
12567  {
12568  sty = stx;
12569  fy = fx;
12570  dy = dx;
12571  }
12572  stx = stp;
12573  fx = fp;
12574  dx = dp;
12575  }
12576 
12577  //
12578  // COMPUTE THE NEW STEP AND SAFEGUARD IT.
12579  //
12580  stpf = Math.Min(stmax, stpf);
12581  stpf = Math.Max(stmin, stpf);
12582  stp = stpf;
12583  if( brackt && bound )
12584  {
12585  if( (double)(sty)>(double)(stx) )
12586  {
12587  stp = Math.Min(stx+0.66*(sty-stx), stp);
12588  }
12589  else
12590  {
12591  stp = Math.Max(stx+0.66*(sty-stx), stp);
12592  }
12593  }
12594  }
12595 
12596 
12597  }
12598  public class xblas
12599  {
12600  /*************************************************************************
12601  More precise dot-product. Absolute error of subroutine result is about
12602  1 ulp of max(MX,V), where:
12603  MX = max( |a[i]*b[i]| )
12604  V = |(a,b)|
12605 
12606  INPUT PARAMETERS
12607  A - array[0..N-1], vector 1
12608  B - array[0..N-1], vector 2
12609  N - vectors length, N<2^29.
12610  Temp - array[0..N-1], pre-allocated temporary storage
12611 
12612  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
12613  R - (A,B)
12614  RErr - estimate of error. This estimate accounts for both errors
12615  during calculation of (A,B) and errors introduced by
12616  rounding of A and B to fit in double (about 1 ulp).
12617 
12618  -- ALGLIB --
12619  Copyright 24.08.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
12620  *************************************************************************/
12621  public static void xdot(double[] a,
12622  double[] b,
12623  int n,
12624  ref double[] temp,
12625  ref double r,
12626  ref double rerr,
12627  alglib.xparams _params)
12628  {
12629  int i = 0;
12630  double mx = 0;
12631  double v = 0;
12632 
12633  r = 0;
12634  rerr = 0;
12635 
12636 
12637  //
12638  // special cases:
12639  // * N=0
12640  //
12641  if( n==0 )
12642  {
12643  r = 0;
12644  rerr = 0;
12645  return;
12646  }
12647  mx = 0;
12648  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
12649  {
12650  v = a[i]*b[i];
12651  temp[i] = v;
12652  mx = Math.Max(mx, Math.Abs(v));
12653  }
12654  if( (double)(mx)==(double)(0) )
12655  {
12656  r = 0;
12657  rerr = 0;
12658  return;
12659  }
12660  xsum(ref temp, mx, n, ref r, ref rerr, _params);
12661  }
12662 
12663 
12664  /*************************************************************************
12665  More precise complex dot-product. Absolute error of subroutine result is
12666  about 1 ulp of max(MX,V), where:
12667  MX = max( |a[i]*b[i]| )
12668  V = |(a,b)|
12669 
12670  INPUT PARAMETERS
12671  A - array[0..N-1], vector 1
12672  B - array[0..N-1], vector 2
12673  N - vectors length, N<2^29.
12674  Temp - array[0..2*N-1], pre-allocated temporary storage
12675 
12676  OUTPUT PARAMETERS
12677  R - (A,B)
12678  RErr - estimate of error. This estimate accounts for both errors
12679  during calculation of (A,B) and errors introduced by
12680  rounding of A and B to fit in double (about 1 ulp).
12681 
12682  -- ALGLIB --
12683  Copyright 27.01.2010 by Bochkanov Sergey
12684  *************************************************************************/
12685  public static void xcdot(complex[] a,
12686  complex[] b,
12687  int n,
12688  ref double[] temp,
12689  ref complex r,
12690  ref double rerr,
12691  alglib.xparams _params)
12692  {
12693  int i = 0;
12694  double mx = 0;
12695  double v = 0;
12696  double rerrx = 0;
12697  double rerry = 0;
12698 
12699  r = 0;
12700  rerr = 0;
12701 
12702 
12703  //
12704  // special cases:
12705  // * N=0
12706  //
12707  if( n==0 )
12708  {
12709  r = 0;
12710  rerr = 0;
12711  return;
12712  }
12713 
12714  //
12715  // calculate real part
12716  //
12717  mx = 0;
12718  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
12719  {
12720  v = a[i].x*b[i].x;
12721  temp[2*i+0] = v;
12722  mx = Math.Max(mx, Math.Abs(v));
12723  v = -(a[i].y*b[i].y);
12724  temp[2*i+1] = v;
12725  mx = Math.Max(mx, Math.Abs(v));
12726  }
12727  if( (double)(mx)==(double)(0) )
12728  {
12729  r.x = 0;
12730  rerrx = 0;
12731  }
12732  else
12733  {
12734  xsum(ref temp, mx, 2*n, ref r.x, ref rerrx, _params);
12735  }
12736 
12737  //
12738  // calculate imaginary part
12739  //
12740  mx = 0;
12741  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
12742  {
12743  v = a[i].x*b[i].y;
12744  temp[2*i+0] = v;
12745  mx = Math.Max(mx, Math.Abs(v));
12746  v = a[i].y*b[i].x;
12747  temp[2*i+1] = v;
12748  mx = Math.Max(mx, Math.Abs(v));
12749  }
12750  if( (double)(mx)==(double)(0) )
12751  {
12752  r.y = 0;
12753  rerry = 0;
12754  }
12755  else
12756  {
12757  xsum(ref temp, mx, 2*n, ref r.y, ref rerry, _params);
12758  }
12759 
12760  //
12761  // total error
12762  //
12763  if( (double)(rerrx)==(double)(0) && (double)(rerry)==(double)(0) )
12764  {
12765  rerr = 0;
12766  }
12767  else
12768  {
12769  rerr = Math.Max(rerrx, rerry)*Math.Sqrt(1+math.sqr(Math.Min(rerrx, rerry)/Math.Max(rerrx, rerry)));
12770  }
12771  }
12772 
12773 
12774  /*************************************************************************
12775  Internal subroutine for extra-precise calculation of SUM(w[i]).
12776 
12777  INPUT PARAMETERS:
12778  W - array[0..N-1], values to be added
12779  W is modified during calculations.
12780  MX - max(W[i])
12781  N - array size
12782 
12783  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
12784  R - SUM(w[i])
12785  RErr- error estimate for R
12786 
12787  -- ALGLIB --
12788  Copyright 24.08.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
12789  *************************************************************************/
12790  private static void xsum(ref double[] w,
12791  double mx,
12792  int n,
12793  ref double r,
12794  ref double rerr,
12795  alglib.xparams _params)
12796  {
12797  int i = 0;
12798  int k = 0;
12799  int ks = 0;
12800  double v = 0;
12801  double s = 0;
12802  double ln2 = 0;
12803  double chunk = 0;
12804  double invchunk = 0;
12805  bool allzeros = new bool();
12806  int i_ = 0;
12807 
12808  r = 0;
12809  rerr = 0;
12810 
12811 
12812  //
12813  // special cases:
12814  // * N=0
12815  // * N is too large to use integer arithmetics
12816  //
12817  if( n==0 )
12818  {
12819  r = 0;
12820  rerr = 0;
12821  return;
12822  }
12823  if( (double)(mx)==(double)(0) )
12824  {
12825  r = 0;
12826  rerr = 0;
12827  return;
12828  }
12829  alglib.ap.assert(n<536870912, "XDot: N is too large!");
12830 
12831  //
12832  // Prepare
12833  //
12834  ln2 = Math.Log(2);
12835  rerr = mx*math.machineepsilon;
12836 
12837  //
12838  // 1. find S such that 0.5<=S*MX<1
12839  // 2. multiply W by S, so task is normalized in some sense
12840  // 3. S:=1/S so we can obtain original vector multiplying by S
12841  //
12842  k = (int)Math.Round(Math.Log(mx)/ln2);
12843  s = xfastpow(2, -k, _params);
12844  if( !math.isfinite(s) )
12845  {
12846 
12847  //
12848  // Overflow or underflow during evaluation of S; fallback low-precision code
12849  //
12850  r = 0;
12851  rerr = mx*math.machineepsilon;
12852  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
12853  {
12854  r = r+w[i];
12855  }
12856  return;
12857  }
12858  while( (double)(s*mx)>=(double)(1) )
12859  {
12860  s = 0.5*s;
12861  }
12862  while( (double)(s*mx)<(double)(0.5) )
12863  {
12864  s = 2*s;
12865  }
12866  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12867  {
12868  w[i_] = s*w[i_];
12869  }
12870  s = 1/s;
12871 
12872  //
12873  // find Chunk=2^M such that N*Chunk<2^29
12874  //
12875  // we have chosen upper limit (2^29) with enough space left
12876  // to tolerate possible problems with rounding and N's close
12877  // to the limit, so we don't want to be very strict here.
12878  //
12879  k = (int)(Math.Log((double)536870912/(double)n)/ln2);
12880  chunk = xfastpow(2, k, _params);
12881  if( (double)(chunk)<(double)(2) )
12882  {
12883  chunk = 2;
12884  }
12885  invchunk = 1/chunk;
12886 
12887  //
12888  // calculate result
12889  //
12890  r = 0;
12891  for(i_=0; i_<=n-1;i_++)
12892  {
12893  w[i_] = chunk*w[i_];
12894  }
12895  while( true )
12896  {
12897  s = s*invchunk;
12898  allzeros = true;
12899  ks = 0;
12900  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
12901  {
12902  v = w[i];
12903  k = (int)(v);
12904  if( (double)(v)!=(double)(k) )
12905  {
12906  allzeros = false;
12907  }
12908  w[i] = chunk*(v-k);
12909  ks = ks+k;
12910  }
12911  r = r+s*ks;
12912  v = Math.Abs(r);
12913  if( allzeros || (double)(s*n+mx)==(double)(mx) )
12914  {
12915  break;
12916  }
12917  }
12918 
12919  //
12920  // correct error
12921  //
12922  rerr = Math.Max(rerr, Math.Abs(r)*math.machineepsilon);
12923  }
12924 
12925 
12926  /*************************************************************************
12927  Fast Pow
12928 
12929  -- ALGLIB --
12930  Copyright 24.08.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
12931  *************************************************************************/
12932  private static double xfastpow(double r,
12933  int n,
12934  alglib.xparams _params)
12935  {
12936  double result = 0;
12937 
12938  result = 0;
12939  if( n>0 )
12940  {
12941  if( n%2==0 )
12942  {
12943  result = math.sqr(xfastpow(r, n/2, _params));
12944  }
12945  else
12946  {
12947  result = r*xfastpow(r, n-1, _params);
12948  }
12949  return result;
12950  }
12951  if( n==0 )
12952  {
12953  result = 1;
12954  }
12955  if( n<0 )
12956  {
12957  result = xfastpow(1/r, -n, _params);
12958  }
12959  return result;
12960  }
12961 
12962 
12963  }
12964  public class basicstatops
12965  {
12966  /*************************************************************************
12967  Internal tied ranking subroutine.
12968 
12969  INPUT PARAMETERS:
12970  X - array to rank
12971  N - array size
12972  IsCentered- whether ranks are centered or not:
12973  * True - ranks are centered in such way that their
12974  sum is zero
12975  * False - ranks are not centered
12976  Buf - temporary buffers
12977 
12978  NOTE: when IsCentered is True and all X[] are equal, this function fills
12979  X by zeros (exact zeros are used, not sum which is only approximately
12980  equal to zero).
12981  *************************************************************************/
12982  public static void rankx(double[] x,
12983  int n,
12984  bool iscentered,
12985  apserv.apbuffers buf,
12986  alglib.xparams _params)
12987  {
12988  int i = 0;
12989  int j = 0;
12990  int k = 0;
12991  double tmp = 0;
12992  double voffs = 0;
12993 
12994 
12995  //
12996  // Prepare
12997  //
12998  if( n<1 )
12999  {
13000  return;
13001  }
13002  if( n==1 )
13003  {
13004  x[0] = 0;
13005  return;
13006  }
13007  if( alglib.ap.len(buf.ra1)<n )
13008  {
13009  buf.ra1 = new double[n];
13010  }
13011  if( alglib.ap.len(buf.ia1)<n )
13012  {
13013  buf.ia1 = new int[n];
13014  }
13015  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
13016  {
13017  buf.ra1[i] = x[i];
13018  buf.ia1[i] = i;
13019  }
13020  tsort.tagsortfasti(ref buf.ra1, ref buf.ia1, ref buf.ra2, ref buf.ia2, n, _params);
13021 
13022  //
13023  // Special test for all values being equal
13024  //
13025  if( (double)(buf.ra1[0])==(double)(buf.ra1[n-1]) )
13026  {
13027  if( iscentered )
13028  {
13029  tmp = 0.0;
13030  }
13031  else
13032  {
13033  tmp = (double)(n-1)/(double)2;
13034  }
13035  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
13036  {
13037  x[i] = tmp;
13038  }
13039  return;
13040  }
13041 
13042  //
13043  // compute tied ranks
13044  //
13045  i = 0;
13046  while( i<=n-1 )
13047  {
13048  j = i+1;
13049  while( j<=n-1 )
13050  {
13051  if( (double)(buf.ra1[j])!=(double)(buf.ra1[i]) )
13052  {
13053  break;
13054  }
13055  j = j+1;
13056  }
13057  for(k=i; k<=j-1; k++)
13058  {
13059  buf.ra1[k] = (double)(i+j-1)/(double)2;
13060  }
13061  i = j;
13062  }
13063 
13064  //
13065  // back to x
13066  //
13067  if( iscentered )
13068  {
13069  voffs = (double)(n-1)/(double)2;
13070  }
13071  else
13072  {
13073  voffs = 0.0;
13074  }
13075  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
13076  {
13077  x[buf.ia1[i]] = buf.ra1[i]-voffs;
13078  }
13079  }
13080 
13081 
13082  /*************************************************************************
13083  Internal untied ranking subroutine.
13084 
13085  INPUT PARAMETERS:
13086  X - array to rank
13087  N - array size
13088  Buf - temporary buffers
13089 
13090  Returns untied ranks (in case of a tie ranks are resolved arbitrarily).
13091  *************************************************************************/
13092  public static void rankxuntied(double[] x,
13093  int n,
13094  apserv.apbuffers buf,
13095  alglib.xparams _params)
13096  {
13097  int i = 0;
13098 
13099 
13100  //
13101  // Prepare
13102  //
13103  if( n<1 )
13104  {
13105  return;
13106  }
13107  if( n==1 )
13108  {
13109  x[0] = 0;
13110  return;
13111  }
13112  if( alglib.ap.len(buf.ra1)<n )
13113  {
13114  buf.ra1 = new double[n];
13115  }
13116  if( alglib.ap.len(buf.ia1)<n )
13117  {
13118  buf.ia1 = new int[n];
13119  }
13120  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
13121  {
13122  buf.ra1[i] = x[i];
13123  buf.ia1[i] = i;
13124  }
13125  tsort.tagsortfasti(ref buf.ra1, ref buf.ia1, ref buf.ra2, ref buf.ia2, n, _params);
13126  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
13127  {
13128  x[buf.ia1[i]] = i;
13129  }
13130  }
13131 
13132 
13133  }

13224  int chunksize = 0;

13304  }
