13393  public class ntheory
13394  {
13395  public static void findprimitiverootandinverse(int n,
13396  ref int proot,
13397  ref int invproot,
13398  alglib.xparams _params)
13399  {
13400  int candroot = 0;
13401  int phin = 0;
13402  int q = 0;
13403  int f = 0;
13404  bool allnonone = new bool();
13405  int x = 0;
13406  int lastx = 0;
13407  int y = 0;
13408  int lasty = 0;
13409  int a = 0;
13410  int b = 0;
13411  int t = 0;
13412  int n2 = 0;
13413 
13414  proot = 0;
13415  invproot = 0;
13416 
13417  alglib.ap.assert(n>=3, "FindPrimitiveRootAndInverse: N<3");
13418  proot = 0;
13419  invproot = 0;
13420 
13421  //
13422  // check that N is prime
13423  //
13424  alglib.ap.assert(isprime(n, _params), "FindPrimitiveRoot: N is not prime");
13425 
13426  //
13427  // Because N is prime, Euler totient function is equal to N-1
13428  //
13429  phin = n-1;
13430 
13431  //
13432  // Test different values of PRoot - from 2 to N-1.
13433  // One of these values MUST be primitive root.
13434  //
13435  // For testing we use algorithm from Wiki (Primitive root modulo n):
13436  // * compute phi(N)
13437  // * determine the different prime factors of phi(N), say p1, ..., pk
13438  // * for every element m of Zn*, compute m^(phi(N)/pi) mod N for i=1..k
13439  // using a fast algorithm for modular exponentiation.
13440  // * a number m for which these k results are all different from 1 is a
13441  // primitive root.
13442  //
13443  for(candroot=2; candroot<=n-1; candroot++)
13444  {
13445 
13446  //
13447  // We have current candidate root in CandRoot.
13448  //
13449  // Scan different prime factors of PhiN. Here:
13450  // * F is a current candidate factor
13451  // * Q is a current quotient - amount which was left after dividing PhiN
13452  // by all previous factors
13453  //
13454  // For each factor, perform test mentioned above.
13455  //
13456  q = phin;
13457  f = 2;
13458  allnonone = true;
13459  while( q>1 )
13460  {
13461  if( q%f==0 )
13462  {
13463  t = modexp(candroot, phin/f, n, _params);
13464  if( t==1 )
13465  {
13466  allnonone = false;
13467  break;
13468  }
13469  while( q%f==0 )
13470  {
13471  q = q/f;
13472  }
13473  }
13474  f = f+1;
13475  }
13476  if( allnonone )
13477  {
13478  proot = candroot;
13479  break;
13480  }
13481  }
13482  alglib.ap.assert(proot>=2, "FindPrimitiveRoot: internal error (root not found)");
13483 
13484  //
13485  // Use extended Euclidean algorithm to find multiplicative inverse of primitive root
13486  //
13487  x = 0;
13488  lastx = 1;
13489  y = 1;
13490  lasty = 0;
13491  a = proot;
13492  b = n;
13493  while( b!=0 )
13494  {
13495  q = a/b;
13496  t = a%b;
13497  a = b;
13498  b = t;
13499  t = lastx-q*x;
13500  lastx = x;
13501  x = t;
13502  t = lasty-q*y;
13503  lasty = y;
13504  y = t;
13505  }
13506  while( lastx<0 )
13507  {
13508  lastx = lastx+n;
13509  }
13510  invproot = lastx;
13511 
13512  //
13513  // Check that it is safe to perform multiplication modulo N.
13514  // Check results for consistency.
13515  //
13516  n2 = (n-1)*(n-1);
13517  alglib.ap.assert(n2/(n-1)==n-1, "FindPrimitiveRoot: internal error");
13518  alglib.ap.assert(proot*invproot/proot==invproot, "FindPrimitiveRoot: internal error");
13519  alglib.ap.assert(proot*invproot/invproot==proot, "FindPrimitiveRoot: internal error");
13520  alglib.ap.assert(proot*invproot%n==1, "FindPrimitiveRoot: internal error");
13521  }
13522 
13523 
13524  private static bool isprime(int n,
13525  alglib.xparams _params)
13526  {
13527  bool result = new bool();
13528  int p = 0;
13529 
13530  result = false;
13531  p = 2;
13532  while( p*p<=n )
13533  {
13534  if( n%p==0 )
13535  {
13536  return result;
13537  }
13538  p = p+1;
13539  }
13540  result = true;
13541  return result;
13542  }
13543 
13544 
13545  private static int modmul(int a,
13546  int b,
13547  int n,
13548  alglib.xparams _params)
13549  {
13550  int result = 0;
13551  int t = 0;
13552  double ra = 0;
13553  double rb = 0;
13554 
13555  alglib.ap.assert(a>=0 && a<n, "ModMul: A<0 or A>=N");
13556  alglib.ap.assert(b>=0 && b<n, "ModMul: B<0 or B>=N");
13557 
13558  //
13559  // Base cases
13560  //
13561  ra = a;
13562  rb = b;
13563  if( b==0 || a==0 )
13564  {
13565  result = 0;
13566  return result;
13567  }
13568  if( b==1 || a==1 )
13569  {
13570  result = a*b;
13571  return result;
13572  }
13573  if( (double)(ra*rb)==(double)(a*b) )
13574  {
13575  result = a*b%n;
13576  return result;
13577  }
13578 
13579  //
13580  // Non-base cases
13581  //
13582  if( b%2==0 )
13583  {
13584 
13585  //
13586  // A*B = (A*(B/2)) * 2
13587  //
13588  // Product T=A*(B/2) is calculated recursively, product T*2 is
13589  // calculated as follows:
13590  // * result:=T-N
13591  // * result:=result+T
13592  // * if result<0 then result:=result+N
13593  //
13594  // In case integer result overflows, we generate exception
13595  //
13596  t = modmul(a, b/2, n, _params);
13597  result = t-n;
13598  result = result+t;
13599  if( result<0 )
13600  {
13601  result = result+n;
13602  }
13603  }
13604  else
13605  {
13606 
13607  //
13608  // A*B = (A*(B div 2)) * 2 + A
13609  //
13610  // Product T=A*(B/2) is calculated recursively, product T*2 is
13611  // calculated as follows:
13612  // * result:=T-N
13613  // * result:=result+T
13614  // * if result<0 then result:=result+N
13615  //
13616  // In case integer result overflows, we generate exception
13617  //
13618  t = modmul(a, b/2, n, _params);
13619  result = t-n;
13620  result = result+t;
13621  if( result<0 )
13622  {
13623  result = result+n;
13624  }
13625  result = result-n;
13626  result = result+a;
13627  if( result<0 )
13628  {
13629  result = result+n;
13630  }
13631  }
13632  return result;
13633  }
13634 
13635 
13636  private static int modexp(int a,
13637  int b,
13638  int n,
13639  alglib.xparams _params)
13640  {
13641  int result = 0;
13642  int t = 0;
13643 
13644  alglib.ap.assert(a>=0 && a<n, "ModExp: A<0 or A>=N");
13645  alglib.ap.assert(b>=0, "ModExp: B<0");
13646 
13647  //
13648  // Base cases
13649  //
13650  if( b==0 )
13651  {
13652  result = 1;
13653  return result;
13654  }
13655  if( b==1 )
13656  {
13657  result = a;
13658  return result;
13659  }
13660 
13661  //
13662  // Non-base cases
13663  //
13664  if( b%2==0 )
13665  {
13666  t = modmul(a, a, n, _params);
13667  result = modexp(t, b/2, n, _params);
13668  }
13669  else
13670  {
13671  t = modmul(a, a, n, _params);
13672  result = modexp(t, b/2, n, _params);
13673  result = modmul(result, a, n, _params);
13674  }
13675  return result;
13676  }
13677 
13678 
13679  }
13680  public class ftbase
13681  {
13682  /*************************************************************************
13683  This record stores execution plan for the fast transformation along with
13684  preallocated temporary buffers and precalculated values.
13685 
13686  FIELDS:
13687  Entries - plan entries, one row = one entry (see below for
13688  description).
13689  Buf0,Buf1,Buf2 - global temporary buffers; some of them are allocated,
13690  some of them are not (as decided by plan generation
13691  subroutine).
13692  Buffer - global buffer whose size is equal to plan size.
13693  There is one-to-one correspondence between elements
13694  of global buffer and elements of array transformed.
13695  Because of it global buffer can be used as temporary
13696  thread-safe storage WITHOUT ACQUIRING LOCK - each
13697  worker thread works with its part of input array,
13698  and each part of input array corresponds to distinct
13699  part of buffer.
13700 
13701  FORMAT OF THE ENTRIES TABLE:
13702 
13703  Entries table is 2D array which stores one entry per row. Row format is:
13704  row[0] operation type:
13705  * 0 for "end of plan/subplan"
13706  * +1 for "reference O(N^2) complex FFT"
13707  * -1 for complex transposition
13708  * -2 for multiplication by twiddle factors of complex FFT
13709  * -3 for "start of plan/subplan"
13710  row[1] repetition count, >=1
13711  row[2] base operand size (number of microvectors), >=1
13712  row[3] microvector size (measured in real numbers), >=1
13713  row[4] parameter0, meaning depends on row[0]
13714  row[5] parameter1, meaning depends on row[0]
13715 
13716  FORMAT OF THE DATA:
13717 
13718  Transformation plan works with row[1]*row[2]*row[3] real numbers, which
13719  are (in most cases) interpreted as sequence of complex numbers. These data
13720  are grouped as follows:
13721  * we have row[1] contiguous OPERANDS, which can be treated separately
13722  * each operand includes row[2] contiguous MICROVECTORS
13723  * each microvector includes row[3] COMPONENTS, which can be treated separately
13724  * pair of components form complex number, so in most cases row[3] will be even
13725 
13726  Say, if you want to perform complex FFT of length 3, then:
13727  * you have 1 operand: row[1]=1
13728  * operand consists of 3 microvectors: row[2]=3
13729  * each microvector has two components: row[3]=2
13730  * a pair of subsequent components is treated as complex number
13731 
13732  if you want to perform TWO simultaneous complex FFT's of length 3, then you
13733  can choose between two representations:
13734  * 1 operand, 3 microvectors, 4 components; storage format is given below:
13735  [ A0X A0Y B0X B0Y A1X A1Y B1X B1Y ... ]
13736  (here A denotes first sequence, B - second one).
13737  * 2 operands, 3 microvectors, 2 components; storage format is given below:
13738  [ A0X A0Y A1X A2Y ... B0X B0Y B1X B1Y ... ]
13739  Most FFT operations are supported only for the second format, but you
13740  should remember that first format sometimes can be used too.
13741 
13742  SUPPORTED OPERATIONS:
13743 
13744  row[0]=0:
13745  * "end of plan/subplan"
13746  * in case we meet entry with such type, FFT transformation is finished
13747  (or we return from recursive FFT subplan, in case it was subplan).
13748 
13749  row[0]=+1:
13750  * "reference 1D complex FFT"
13751  * we perform reference O(N^2) complex FFT on input data, which are treated
13752  as row[1] arrays, each of row[2] complex numbers, and row[3] must be
13753  equal to 2
13754  * transformation is performed using temporary buffer
13755 
13756  row[0]=opBluesteinsFFT:
13757  * input array is handled with Bluestein's algorithm (by zero-padding to
13758  Param0 complex numbers).
13759  * this plan calls Param0-point subplan which is located at offset Param1
13760  (offset is measured with respect to location of the calling entry)
13761  * this plan uses precomputed quantities stored in Plan.PrecR at
13762  offset Param2.
13763  * transformation is performed using 4 temporary buffers, which are
13764  retrieved from Plan.BluesteinPool.
13765 
13766  row[0]=+3:
13767  * "optimized 1D complex FFT"
13768  * this function supports only several operand sizes: from 1 to 5.
13769  These transforms are hard-coded and performed very efficiently
13770 
13771  row[0]=opRadersFFT:
13772  * input array is handled with Rader's algorithm (permutation and
13773  reduction to N-1-point FFT)
13774  * this plan calls N-1-point subplan which is located at offset Param0
13775  (offset is measured with respect to location of the calling entry)
13776  * this plan uses precomputed primitive root and its inverse (modulo N)
13777  which are stored in Param1 and Param2.
13778  * Param3 stores offset of the precomputed data for the plan
13779  * plan length must be prime, (N-1)*(N-1) must fit into integer variable
13780 
13781  row[0]=-1
13782  * "complex transposition"
13783  * input data are treated as row[1] independent arrays, which are processed
13784  separately
13785  * each of operands is treated as matrix with row[4] rows and row[2]/row[4]
13786  columns. Each element of the matrix is microvector with row[3] components.
13787  * transposition is performed using temporary buffer
13788 
13789  row[0]=-2
13790  * "multiplication by twiddle factors of complex FFT"
13791  * input data are treated as row[1] independent arrays, which are processed
13792  separately
13793  * row[4] contains N1 - length of the "first FFT" in a Cooley-Tukey FFT
13794  algorithm
13795  * this function does not require temporary buffers
13796 
13797  row[0]=-3
13798  * "start of the plan"
13799  * each subplan must start from this entry
13800  * param0 is ignored
13801  * param1 stores approximate (optimistic) estimate of KFLOPs required to
13802  transform one operand of the plan. Total cost of the plan is approximately
13803  equal to row[1]*param1 KFLOPs.
13804  * this function does not require temporary buffers
13805 
13806  row[0]=-4
13807  * "jump"
13808  * param0 stores relative offset of the jump site
13809  (+1 corresponds to the next entry)
13810 
13811  row[0]=-5
13812  * "parallel call"
13813  * input data are treated as row[1] independent arrays
13814  * child subplan is applied independently for each of arrays - row[1] times
13815  * subplan length must be equal to row[2]*row[3]
13816  * param0 stores relative offset of the child subplan site
13817  (+1 corresponds to the next entry)
13818  * param1 stores approximate total cost of plan, measured in UNITS
13819  (1 UNIT = 100 KFLOPs). Plan cost must be rounded DOWN to nearest integer.
13820 
13821 
13822 
13823  TODO
13824  2. from KFLOPs to UNITs, 1 UNIT = 100 000 FLOP!!!!!!!!!!!
13825 
13826  3. from IsRoot to TaskType = {0, -1, +1}; or maybe, add IsSeparatePlan
13827  to distinguish root of child subplan from global root which uses
13828  separate buffer
13829 
13830  4. child subplans in parallel call must NOT use buffer provided by parent plan;
13831  they must allocate their own local buffer
13832  *************************************************************************/
13833  public class fasttransformplan : apobject
13834  {
13835  public int[,] entries;
13836  public double[] buffer;
13837  public double[] precr;
13838  public double[] preci;
13839  public alglib.smp.shared_pool bluesteinpool;
13840  public fasttransformplan()
13841  {
13842  init();
13843  }
13844  public override void init()
13845  {
13846  entries = new int[0,0];
13847  buffer = new double[0];
13848  precr = new double[0];
13849  preci = new double[0];
13850  bluesteinpool = new alglib.smp.shared_pool();
13851  }
13852  public override alglib.apobject make_copy()
13853  {
13854  fasttransformplan _result = new fasttransformplan();
13855  _result.entries = (int[,])entries.Clone();
13856  _result.buffer = (double[])buffer.Clone();
13857  _result.precr = (double[])precr.Clone();
13858  _result.preci = (double[])preci.Clone();
13859  _result.bluesteinpool = (alglib.smp.shared_pool)bluesteinpool.make_copy();
13860  return _result;
13861  }
13862  };
13863 
13864 
13865 
13866 
13867  public const int coltype = 0;
13868  public const int coloperandscnt = 1;
13869  public const int coloperandsize = 2;
13870  public const int colmicrovectorsize = 3;
13871  public const int colparam0 = 4;
13872  public const int colparam1 = 5;
13873  public const int colparam2 = 6;
13874  public const int colparam3 = 7;
13875  public const int colscnt = 8;
13876  public const int opend = 0;
13877  public const int opcomplexreffft = 1;
13878  public const int opbluesteinsfft = 2;
13879  public const int opcomplexcodeletfft = 3;
13880  public const int opcomplexcodelettwfft = 4;
13881  public const int opradersfft = 5;
13882  public const int opcomplextranspose = -1;
13883  public const int opcomplexfftfactors = -2;
13884  public const int opstart = -3;
13885  public const int opjmp = -4;
13886  public const int opparallelcall = -5;
13887  public const int maxradix = 6;
13888  public const int updatetw = 16;
13889  public const int recursivethreshold = 1024;
13890  public const int raderthreshold = 19;
13891  public const int ftbasecodeletrecommended = 5;
13892  public const double ftbaseinefficiencyfactor = 1.3;
13893  public const int ftbasemaxsmoothfactor = 5;
13894 
13895 
13896  /*************************************************************************
13897  This subroutine generates FFT plan for K complex FFT's with length N each.
13898 
13899  INPUT PARAMETERS:
13900  N - FFT length (in complex numbers), N>=1
13901  K - number of repetitions, K>=1
13902 
13903  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
13904  Plan - plan
13905 
13906  -- ALGLIB --
13907  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
13908  *************************************************************************/
13909  public static void ftcomplexfftplan(int n,
13910  int k,
13911  fasttransformplan plan,
13912  alglib.xparams _params)
13913  {
13914  apserv.srealarray bluesteinbuf = new apserv.srealarray();
13915  int rowptr = 0;
13916  int bluesteinsize = 0;
13917  int precrptr = 0;
13918  int preciptr = 0;
13919  int precrsize = 0;
13920  int precisize = 0;
13921 
13922 
13923  //
13924  // Initial check for parameters
13925  //
13926  alglib.ap.assert(n>0, "FTComplexFFTPlan: N<=0");
13927  alglib.ap.assert(k>0, "FTComplexFFTPlan: K<=0");
13928 
13929  //
13930  // Determine required sizes of precomputed real and integer
13931  // buffers. This stage of code is highly dependent on internals
13932  // of FTComplexFFTPlanRec() and must be kept synchronized with
13933  // possible changes in internals of plan generation function.
13934  //
13935  // Buffer size is determined as follows:
13936  // * N is factorized
13937  // * we factor out anything which is less or equal to MaxRadix
13938  // * prime factor F>RaderThreshold requires 4*FTBaseFindSmooth(2*F-1)
13939  // real entries to store precomputed Quantities for Bluestein's
13940  // transformation
13941  // * prime factor F<=RaderThreshold does NOT require
13942  // precomputed storage
13943  //
13944  precrsize = 0;
13945  precisize = 0;
13946  ftdeterminespacerequirements(n, ref precrsize, ref precisize, _params);
13947  if( precrsize>0 )
13948  {
13949  plan.precr = new double[precrsize];
13950  }
13951  if( precisize>0 )
13952  {
13953  plan.preci = new double[precisize];
13954  }
13955 
13956  //
13957  // Generate plan
13958  //
13959  rowptr = 0;
13960  precrptr = 0;
13961  preciptr = 0;
13962  bluesteinsize = 1;
13963  plan.buffer = new double[2*n*k];
13964  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n, k, true, true, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
13965  bluesteinbuf.val = new double[bluesteinsize];
13966  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_set_seed(plan.bluesteinpool, bluesteinbuf);
13967 
13968  //
13969  // Check that actual amount of precomputed space used by transformation
13970  // plan is EXACTLY equal to amount of space allocated by us.
13971  //
13972  alglib.ap.assert(precrptr==precrsize, "FTComplexFFTPlan: internal error (PrecRPtr<>PrecRSize)");
13973  alglib.ap.assert(preciptr==precisize, "FTComplexFFTPlan: internal error (PrecRPtr<>PrecRSize)");
13974  }
13975 
13976 
13977  /*************************************************************************
13978  This subroutine applies transformation plan to input/output array A.
13979 
13980  INPUT PARAMETERS:
13981  Plan - transformation plan
13982  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
13983  OffsA - offset of the subarray to process
13984  RepCnt - repetition count (transformation is repeatedly applied
13985  to subsequent subarrays)
13986 
13987  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
13988  Plan - plan (temporary buffers can be modified, plan itself
13989  is unchanged and can be reused)
13990  A - transformed array
13991 
13992  -- ALGLIB --
13993  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
13994  *************************************************************************/
13995  public static void ftapplyplan(fasttransformplan plan,
13996  double[] a,
13997  int offsa,
13998  int repcnt,
13999  alglib.xparams _params)
14000  {
14001  int plansize = 0;
14002  int i = 0;
14003 
14004  plansize = plan.entries[0,coloperandscnt]*plan.entries[0,coloperandsize]*plan.entries[0,colmicrovectorsize];
14005  for(i=0; i<=repcnt-1; i++)
14006  {
14007  ftapplysubplan(plan, 0, a, offsa+plansize*i, 0, plan.buffer, 1, _params);
14008  }
14009  }
14010 
14011 
14012  /*************************************************************************
14013  Returns good factorization N=N1*N2.
14014 
14015  Usually N1<=N2 (but not always - small N's may be exception).
14016  if N1<>1 then N2<>1.
14017 
14018  Factorization is chosen depending on task type and codelets we have.
14019 
14020  -- ALGLIB --
14021  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
14022  *************************************************************************/
14023  public static void ftbasefactorize(int n,
14024  int tasktype,
14025  ref int n1,
14026  ref int n2,
14027  alglib.xparams _params)
14028  {
14029  int j = 0;
14030 
14031  n1 = 0;
14032  n2 = 0;
14033 
14034  n1 = 0;
14035  n2 = 0;
14036 
14037  //
14038  // try to find good codelet
14039  //
14040  if( n1*n2!=n )
14041  {
14042  for(j=ftbasecodeletrecommended; j>=2; j--)
14043  {
14044  if( n%j==0 )
14045  {
14046  n1 = j;
14047  n2 = n/j;
14048  break;
14049  }
14050  }
14051  }
14052 
14053  //
14054  // try to factorize N
14055  //
14056  if( n1*n2!=n )
14057  {
14058  for(j=ftbasecodeletrecommended+1; j<=n-1; j++)
14059  {
14060  if( n%j==0 )
14061  {
14062  n1 = j;
14063  n2 = n/j;
14064  break;
14065  }
14066  }
14067  }
14068 
14069  //
14070  // looks like N is prime :(
14071  //
14072  if( n1*n2!=n )
14073  {
14074  n1 = 1;
14075  n2 = n;
14076  }
14077 
14078  //
14079  // normalize
14080  //
14081  if( n2==1 && n1!=1 )
14082  {
14083  n2 = n1;
14084  n1 = 1;
14085  }
14086  }
14087 
14088 
14089  /*************************************************************************
14090  Is number smooth?
14091 
14092  -- ALGLIB --
14093  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
14094  *************************************************************************/
14095  public static bool ftbaseissmooth(int n,
14096  alglib.xparams _params)
14097  {
14098  bool result = new bool();
14099  int i = 0;
14100 
14101  for(i=2; i<=ftbasemaxsmoothfactor; i++)
14102  {
14103  while( n%i==0 )
14104  {
14105  n = n/i;
14106  }
14107  }
14108  result = n==1;
14109  return result;
14110  }
14111 
14112 
14113  /*************************************************************************
14114  Returns smallest smooth (divisible only by 2, 3, 5) number that is greater
14115  than or equal to max(N,2)
14116 
14117  -- ALGLIB --
14118  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
14119  *************************************************************************/
14120  public static int ftbasefindsmooth(int n,
14121  alglib.xparams _params)
14122  {
14123  int result = 0;
14124  int best = 0;
14125 
14126  best = 2;
14127  while( best<n )
14128  {
14129  best = 2*best;
14130  }
14131  ftbasefindsmoothrec(n, 1, 2, ref best, _params);
14132  result = best;
14133  return result;
14134  }
14135 
14136 
14137  /*************************************************************************
14138  Returns smallest smooth (divisible only by 2, 3, 5) even number that is
14139  greater than or equal to max(N,2)
14140 
14141  -- ALGLIB --
14142  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
14143  *************************************************************************/
14144  public static int ftbasefindsmootheven(int n,
14145  alglib.xparams _params)
14146  {
14147  int result = 0;
14148  int best = 0;
14149 
14150  best = 2;
14151  while( best<n )
14152  {
14153  best = 2*best;
14154  }
14155  ftbasefindsmoothrec(n, 2, 2, ref best, _params);
14156  result = best;
14157  return result;
14158  }
14159 
14160 
14161  /*************************************************************************
14162  Returns estimate of FLOP count for the FFT.
14163 
14164  It is only an estimate based on operations count for the PERFECT FFT
14165  and relative inefficiency of the algorithm actually used.
14166 
14167  N should be power of 2, estimates are badly wrong for non-power-of-2 N's.
14168 
14169  -- ALGLIB --
14170  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
14171  *************************************************************************/
14172  public static double ftbasegetflopestimate(int n,
14173  alglib.xparams _params)
14174  {
14175  double result = 0;
14176 
14177  result = ftbaseinefficiencyfactor*(4*n*Math.Log(n)/Math.Log(2)-6*n+8);
14178  return result;
14179  }
14180 
14181 
14182  /*************************************************************************
14183  This function returns EXACT estimate of the space requirements for N-point
14184  FFT. Internals of this function are highly dependent on details of different
14185  FFTs employed by this unit, so every time algorithm is changed this function
14186  has to be rewritten.
14187 
14188  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14189  N - transform length
14190  PrecRSize - must be set to zero
14191  PrecISize - must be set to zero
14192 
14193  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14194  PrecRSize - number of real temporaries required for transformation
14195  PrecISize - number of integer temporaries required for transformation
14196 
14197 
14198  -- ALGLIB --
14199  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14200  *************************************************************************/
14201  private static void ftdeterminespacerequirements(int n,
14202  ref int precrsize,
14203  ref int precisize,
14204  alglib.xparams _params)
14205  {
14206  int ncur = 0;
14207  int f = 0;
14208  int i = 0;
14209 
14210 
14211  //
14212  // Determine required sizes of precomputed real and integer
14213  // buffers. This stage of code is highly dependent on internals
14214  // of FTComplexFFTPlanRec() and must be kept synchronized with
14215  // possible changes in internals of plan generation function.
14216  //
14217  // Buffer size is determined as follows:
14218  // * N is factorized
14219  // * we factor out anything which is less or equal to MaxRadix
14220  // * prime factor F>RaderThreshold requires 4*FTBaseFindSmooth(2*F-1)
14221  // real entries to store precomputed Quantities for Bluestein's
14222  // transformation
14223  // * prime factor F<=RaderThreshold requires 2*(F-1)+ESTIMATE(F-1)
14224  // precomputed storage
14225  //
14226  ncur = n;
14227  for(i=2; i<=maxradix; i++)
14228  {
14229  while( ncur%i==0 )
14230  {
14231  ncur = ncur/i;
14232  }
14233  }
14234  f = 2;
14235  while( f<=ncur )
14236  {
14237  while( ncur%f==0 )
14238  {
14239  if( f>raderthreshold )
14240  {
14241  precrsize = precrsize+4*ftbasefindsmooth(2*f-1, _params);
14242  }
14243  else
14244  {
14245  precrsize = precrsize+2*(f-1);
14246  ftdeterminespacerequirements(f-1, ref precrsize, ref precisize, _params);
14247  }
14248  ncur = ncur/f;
14249  }
14250  f = f+1;
14251  }
14252  }
14253 
14254 
14255  /*************************************************************************
14256  Recurrent function called by FTComplexFFTPlan() and other functions. It
14257  recursively builds transformation plan
14258 
14259  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14260  N - FFT length (in complex numbers), N>=1
14261  K - number of repetitions, K>=1
14262  ChildPlan - if True, plan generator inserts OpStart/opEnd in the
14263  plan header/footer.
14264  TopmostPlan - if True, plan generator assumes that it is topmost plan:
14265  * it may use global buffer for transpositions
14266  and there is no other plan which executes in parallel
14267  RowPtr - index which points to past-the-last entry generated so far
14268  BluesteinSize- amount of storage (in real numbers) required for Bluestein buffer
14269  PrecRPtr - pointer to unused part of precomputed real buffer (Plan.PrecR):
14270  * when this function stores some data to precomputed buffer,
14271  it advances pointer.
14272  * it is responsibility of the function to assert that
14273  Plan.PrecR has enough space to store data before actually
14274  writing to buffer.
14275  * it is responsibility of the caller to allocate enough
14276  space before calling this function
14277  PrecIPtr - pointer to unused part of precomputed integer buffer (Plan.PrecI):
14278  * when this function stores some data to precomputed buffer,
14279  it advances pointer.
14280  * it is responsibility of the function to assert that
14281  Plan.PrecR has enough space to store data before actually
14282  writing to buffer.
14283  * it is responsibility of the caller to allocate enough
14284  space before calling this function
14285  Plan - plan (generated so far)
14286 
14287  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14288  RowPtr - updated pointer (advanced by number of entries generated
14289  by function)
14290  BluesteinSize- updated amount
14291  (may be increased, but may never be decreased)
14292 
14293  NOTE: in case TopmostPlan is True, ChildPlan is also must be True.
14294 
14295  -- ALGLIB --
14296  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14297  *************************************************************************/
14298  private static void ftcomplexfftplanrec(int n,
14299  int k,
14300  bool childplan,
14301  bool topmostplan,
14302  ref int rowptr,
14303  ref int bluesteinsize,
14304  ref int precrptr,
14305  ref int preciptr,
14306  fasttransformplan plan,
14307  alglib.xparams _params)
14308  {
14309  apserv.srealarray localbuf = new apserv.srealarray();
14310  int m = 0;
14311  int n1 = 0;
14312  int n2 = 0;
14313  int gq = 0;
14314  int giq = 0;
14315  int row0 = 0;
14316  int row1 = 0;
14317  int row2 = 0;
14318  int row3 = 0;
14319 
14320  alglib.ap.assert(n>0, "FTComplexFFTPlan: N<=0");
14321  alglib.ap.assert(k>0, "FTComplexFFTPlan: K<=0");
14322  alglib.ap.assert(!topmostplan || childplan, "FTComplexFFTPlan: ChildPlan is inconsistent with TopmostPlan");
14323 
14324  //
14325  // Try to generate "topmost" plan
14326  //
14327  if( topmostplan && n>recursivethreshold )
14328  {
14329  ftfactorize(n, false, ref n1, ref n2, _params);
14330  if( n1*n2==0 )
14331  {
14332 
14333  //
14334  // Handle prime-factor FFT with Bluestein's FFT.
14335  // Determine size of Bluestein's buffer.
14336  //
14337  m = ftbasefindsmooth(2*n-1, _params);
14338  bluesteinsize = Math.Max(2*m, bluesteinsize);
14339 
14340  //
14341  // Generate plan
14342  //
14343  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14344  ftpushentry4(plan, ref rowptr, opbluesteinsfft, k, n, 2, m, 2, precrptr, 0, _params);
14345  row0 = rowptr;
14346  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opjmp, 0, 0, 0, 0, _params);
14347  ftcomplexfftplanrec(m, 1, true, true, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14348  row1 = rowptr;
14349  plan.entries[row0,colparam0] = row1-row0;
14350  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14351 
14352  //
14353  // Fill precomputed buffer
14354  //
14355  ftprecomputebluesteinsfft(n, m, plan.precr, precrptr, _params);
14356 
14357  //
14358  // Update pointer to the precomputed area
14359  //
14360  precrptr = precrptr+4*m;
14361  }
14362  else
14363  {
14364 
14365  //
14366  // Handle composite FFT with recursive Cooley-Tukey which
14367  // uses global buffer instead of local one.
14368  //
14369  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14370  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14371  row0 = rowptr;
14372  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opparallelcall, k*n2, n1, 2, 0, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14373  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplexfftfactors, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14374  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n2, _params);
14375  row2 = rowptr;
14376  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opparallelcall, k*n1, n2, 2, 0, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14377  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14378  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14379  row1 = rowptr;
14380  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n1, 1, true, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14381  plan.entries[row0,colparam0] = row1-row0;
14382  row3 = rowptr;
14383  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n2, 1, true, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14384  plan.entries[row2,colparam0] = row3-row2;
14385  }
14386  return;
14387  }
14388 
14389  //
14390  // Prepare "non-topmost" plan:
14391  // * calculate factorization
14392  // * use local (shared) buffer
14393  // * update buffer size - ANY plan will need at least
14394  // 2*N temporaries, additional requirements can be
14395  // applied later
14396  //
14397  ftfactorize(n, false, ref n1, ref n2, _params);
14398 
14399  //
14400  // Handle FFT's with N1*N2=0: either small-N or prime-factor
14401  //
14402  if( n1*n2==0 )
14403  {
14404  if( n<=maxradix )
14405  {
14406 
14407  //
14408  // Small-N FFT
14409  //
14410  if( childplan )
14411  {
14412  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14413  }
14414  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplexcodeletfft, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14415  if( childplan )
14416  {
14417  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14418  }
14419  return;
14420  }
14421  if( n<=raderthreshold )
14422  {
14423 
14424  //
14425  // Handle prime-factor FFT's with Rader's FFT
14426  //
14427  m = n-1;
14428  if( childplan )
14429  {
14430  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14431  }
14432  ntheory.findprimitiverootandinverse(n, ref gq, ref giq, _params);
14433  ftpushentry4(plan, ref rowptr, opradersfft, k, n, 2, 2, gq, giq, precrptr, _params);
14434  ftprecomputeradersfft(n, gq, giq, plan.precr, precrptr, _params);
14435  precrptr = precrptr+2*(n-1);
14436  row0 = rowptr;
14437  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opjmp, 0, 0, 0, 0, _params);
14438  ftcomplexfftplanrec(m, 1, true, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14439  row1 = rowptr;
14440  plan.entries[row0,colparam0] = row1-row0;
14441  if( childplan )
14442  {
14443  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14444  }
14445  }
14446  else
14447  {
14448 
14449  //
14450  // Handle prime-factor FFT's with Bluestein's FFT
14451  //
14452  m = ftbasefindsmooth(2*n-1, _params);
14453  bluesteinsize = Math.Max(2*m, bluesteinsize);
14454  if( childplan )
14455  {
14456  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14457  }
14458  ftpushentry4(plan, ref rowptr, opbluesteinsfft, k, n, 2, m, 2, precrptr, 0, _params);
14459  ftprecomputebluesteinsfft(n, m, plan.precr, precrptr, _params);
14460  precrptr = precrptr+4*m;
14461  row0 = rowptr;
14462  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opjmp, 0, 0, 0, 0, _params);
14463  ftcomplexfftplanrec(m, 1, true, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14464  row1 = rowptr;
14465  plan.entries[row0,colparam0] = row1-row0;
14466  if( childplan )
14467  {
14468  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14469  }
14470  }
14471  return;
14472  }
14473 
14474  //
14475  // Handle Cooley-Tukey FFT with small N1
14476  //
14477  if( n1<=maxradix )
14478  {
14479 
14480  //
14481  // Specialized transformation for small N1:
14482  // * N2 short inplace FFT's, each N1-point, with integrated twiddle factors
14483  // * N1 long FFT's
14484  // * final transposition
14485  //
14486  if( childplan )
14487  {
14488  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14489  }
14490  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplexcodelettwfft, k, n1, 2*n2, 0, _params);
14491  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n2, k*n1, false, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14492  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14493  if( childplan )
14494  {
14495  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14496  }
14497  return;
14498  }
14499 
14500  //
14501  // Handle general Cooley-Tukey FFT, either "flat" or "recursive"
14502  //
14503  if( n<=recursivethreshold )
14504  {
14505 
14506  //
14507  // General code for large N1/N2, "flat" version without explicit recurrence
14508  // (nested subplans are inserted directly into the body of the plan)
14509  //
14510  if( childplan )
14511  {
14512  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14513  }
14514  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14515  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n1, k*n2, false, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14516  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplexfftfactors, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14517  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n2, _params);
14518  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n2, k*n1, false, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14519  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14520  if( childplan )
14521  {
14522  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14523  }
14524  }
14525  else
14526  {
14527 
14528  //
14529  // General code for large N1/N2, "recursive" version - nested subplans
14530  // are separated from the plan body.
14531  //
14532  // Generate parent plan.
14533  //
14534  if( childplan )
14535  {
14536  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opstart, k, n, 2, -1, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14537  }
14538  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14539  row0 = rowptr;
14540  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opparallelcall, k*n2, n1, 2, 0, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14541  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplexfftfactors, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14542  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n2, _params);
14543  row2 = rowptr;
14544  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, opparallelcall, k*n1, n2, 2, 0, ftoptimisticestimate(n, _params), _params);
14545  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opcomplextranspose, k, n, 2, n1, _params);
14546  if( childplan )
14547  {
14548  ftpushentry(plan, ref rowptr, opend, k, n, 2, 0, _params);
14549  }
14550 
14551  //
14552  // Generate child subplans, insert refence to parent plans
14553  //
14554  row1 = rowptr;
14555  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n1, 1, true, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14556  plan.entries[row0,colparam0] = row1-row0;
14557  row3 = rowptr;
14558  ftcomplexfftplanrec(n2, 1, true, false, ref rowptr, ref bluesteinsize, ref precrptr, ref preciptr, plan, _params);
14559  plan.entries[row2,colparam0] = row3-row2;
14560  }
14561  }
14562 
14563 
14564  /*************************************************************************
14565  This function pushes one more entry to the plan. It resizes Entries matrix
14566  if needed.
14567 
14568  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14569  Plan - plan (generated so far)
14570  RowPtr - index which points to past-the-last entry generated so far
14571  EType - entry type
14572  EOpCnt - operands count
14573  EOpSize - operand size
14574  EMcvSize - microvector size
14575  EParam0 - parameter 0
14576 
14577  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14578  Plan - updated plan
14579  RowPtr - updated pointer
14580 
14581  NOTE: Param1 is set to -1.
14582 
14583  -- ALGLIB --
14584  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14585  *************************************************************************/
14586  private static void ftpushentry(fasttransformplan plan,
14587  ref int rowptr,
14588  int etype,
14589  int eopcnt,
14590  int eopsize,
14591  int emcvsize,
14592  int eparam0,
14593  alglib.xparams _params)
14594  {
14595  ftpushentry2(plan, ref rowptr, etype, eopcnt, eopsize, emcvsize, eparam0, -1, _params);
14596  }
14597 
14598 
14599  /*************************************************************************
14600  Same as FTPushEntry(), but sets Param0 AND Param1.
14601  This function pushes one more entry to the plan. It resized Entries matrix
14602  if needed.
14603 
14604  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14605  Plan - plan (generated so far)
14606  RowPtr - index which points to past-the-last entry generated so far
14607  EType - entry type
14608  EOpCnt - operands count
14609  EOpSize - operand size
14610  EMcvSize - microvector size
14611  EParam0 - parameter 0
14612  EParam1 - parameter 1
14613 
14614  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14615  Plan - updated plan
14616  RowPtr - updated pointer
14617 
14618  -- ALGLIB --
14619  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14620  *************************************************************************/
14621  private static void ftpushentry2(fasttransformplan plan,
14622  ref int rowptr,
14623  int etype,
14624  int eopcnt,
14625  int eopsize,
14626  int emcvsize,
14627  int eparam0,
14628  int eparam1,
14629  alglib.xparams _params)
14630  {
14631  if( rowptr>=alglib.ap.rows(plan.entries) )
14632  {
14633  apserv.imatrixresize(ref plan.entries, Math.Max(2*alglib.ap.rows(plan.entries), 1), colscnt, _params);
14634  }
14635  plan.entries[rowptr,coltype] = etype;
14636  plan.entries[rowptr,coloperandscnt] = eopcnt;
14637  plan.entries[rowptr,coloperandsize] = eopsize;
14638  plan.entries[rowptr,colmicrovectorsize] = emcvsize;
14639  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam0] = eparam0;
14640  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam1] = eparam1;
14641  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam2] = 0;
14642  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam3] = 0;
14643  rowptr = rowptr+1;
14644  }
14645 
14646 
14647  /*************************************************************************
14648  Same as FTPushEntry(), but sets Param0, Param1, Param2 and Param3.
14649  This function pushes one more entry to the plan. It resized Entries matrix
14650  if needed.
14651 
14652  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14653  Plan - plan (generated so far)
14654  RowPtr - index which points to past-the-last entry generated so far
14655  EType - entry type
14656  EOpCnt - operands count
14657  EOpSize - operand size
14658  EMcvSize - microvector size
14659  EParam0 - parameter 0
14660  EParam1 - parameter 1
14661  EParam2 - parameter 2
14662  EParam3 - parameter 3
14663 
14664  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14665  Plan - updated plan
14666  RowPtr - updated pointer
14667 
14668  -- ALGLIB --
14669  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14670  *************************************************************************/
14671  private static void ftpushentry4(fasttransformplan plan,
14672  ref int rowptr,
14673  int etype,
14674  int eopcnt,
14675  int eopsize,
14676  int emcvsize,
14677  int eparam0,
14678  int eparam1,
14679  int eparam2,
14680  int eparam3,
14681  alglib.xparams _params)
14682  {
14683  if( rowptr>=alglib.ap.rows(plan.entries) )
14684  {
14685  apserv.imatrixresize(ref plan.entries, Math.Max(2*alglib.ap.rows(plan.entries), 1), colscnt, _params);
14686  }
14687  plan.entries[rowptr,coltype] = etype;
14688  plan.entries[rowptr,coloperandscnt] = eopcnt;
14689  plan.entries[rowptr,coloperandsize] = eopsize;
14690  plan.entries[rowptr,colmicrovectorsize] = emcvsize;
14691  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam0] = eparam0;
14692  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam1] = eparam1;
14693  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam2] = eparam2;
14694  plan.entries[rowptr,colparam3] = eparam3;
14695  rowptr = rowptr+1;
14696  }
14697 
14698 
14699  /*************************************************************************
14700  This subroutine applies subplan to input/output array A.
14701 
14702  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14703  Plan - transformation plan
14704  SubPlan - subplan index
14705  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
14706  ABase - base offset in array A, this value points to start of
14707  subarray whose length is equal to length of the plan
14708  AOffset - offset with respect to ABase, 0<=AOffset<PlanLength.
14709  This is an offset within large PlanLength-subarray of
14710  the chunk to process.
14711  Buf - temporary buffer whose length is equal to plan length
14712  (without taking into account RepCnt) or larger.
14713  OffsBuf - offset in the buffer array
14714  RepCnt - repetition count (transformation is repeatedly applied
14715  to subsequent subarrays)
14716 
14717  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14718  Plan - plan (temporary buffers can be modified, plan itself
14719  is unchanged and can be reused)
14720  A - transformed array
14721 
14722  -- ALGLIB --
14723  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14724  *************************************************************************/
14725  private static void ftapplysubplan(fasttransformplan plan,
14726  int subplan,
14727  double[] a,
14728  int abase,
14729  int aoffset,
14730  double[] buf,
14731  int repcnt,
14732  alglib.xparams _params)
14733  {
14734  int rowidx = 0;
14735  int i = 0;
14736  int n1 = 0;
14737  int n2 = 0;
14738  int operation = 0;
14739  int operandscnt = 0;
14740  int operandsize = 0;
14741  int microvectorsize = 0;
14742  int param0 = 0;
14743  int param1 = 0;
14744  int parentsize = 0;
14745  int childsize = 0;
14746  int chunksize = 0;
14747  int lastchunksize = 0;
14748  apserv.srealarray bufa = null;
14749  apserv.srealarray bufb = null;
14750  apserv.srealarray bufc = null;
14751  apserv.srealarray bufd = null;
14752 
14753  alglib.ap.assert(plan.entries[subplan,coltype]==opstart, "FTApplySubPlan: incorrect subplan header");
14754  rowidx = subplan+1;
14755  while( plan.entries[rowidx,coltype]!=opend )
14756  {
14757  operation = plan.entries[rowidx,coltype];
14758  operandscnt = repcnt*plan.entries[rowidx,coloperandscnt];
14759  operandsize = plan.entries[rowidx,coloperandsize];
14760  microvectorsize = plan.entries[rowidx,colmicrovectorsize];
14761  param0 = plan.entries[rowidx,colparam0];
14762  param1 = plan.entries[rowidx,colparam1];
14763  apserv.touchint(ref param1, _params);
14764 
14765  //
14766  // Process "jump" operation
14767  //
14768  if( operation==opjmp )
14769  {
14770  rowidx = rowidx+plan.entries[rowidx,colparam0];
14771  continue;
14772  }
14773 
14774  //
14775  // Process "parallel call" operation:
14776  // * we perform initial check for consistency between parent and child plans
14777  // * we call FTSplitAndApplyParallelPlan(), which splits parallel plan into
14778  // several parallel tasks
14779  //
14780  if( operation==opparallelcall )
14781  {
14782  parentsize = operandsize*microvectorsize;
14783  childsize = plan.entries[rowidx+param0,coloperandscnt]*plan.entries[rowidx+param0,coloperandsize]*plan.entries[rowidx+param0,colmicrovectorsize];
14784  alglib.ap.assert(plan.entries[rowidx+param0,coltype]==opstart, "FTApplySubPlan: incorrect child subplan header");
14785  alglib.ap.assert(parentsize==childsize, "FTApplySubPlan: incorrect child subplan header");
14786  chunksize = Math.Max(recursivethreshold/childsize, 1);
14787  lastchunksize = operandscnt%chunksize;
14788  if( lastchunksize==0 )
14789  {
14790  lastchunksize = chunksize;
14791  }
14792  i = 0;
14793  while( i<operandscnt )
14794  {
14795  chunksize = Math.Min(chunksize, operandscnt-i);
14796  ftapplysubplan(plan, rowidx+param0, a, abase, aoffset+i*childsize, buf, chunksize, _params);
14797  i = i+chunksize;
14798  }
14799  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14800  continue;
14801  }
14802 
14803  //
14804  // Process "reference complex FFT" operation
14805  //
14806  if( operation==opcomplexreffft )
14807  {
14808  ftapplycomplexreffft(a, abase+aoffset, operandscnt, operandsize, microvectorsize, buf, _params);
14809  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14810  continue;
14811  }
14812 
14813  //
14814  // Process "codelet FFT" operation
14815  //
14816  if( operation==opcomplexcodeletfft )
14817  {
14818  ftapplycomplexcodeletfft(a, abase+aoffset, operandscnt, operandsize, microvectorsize, _params);
14819  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14820  continue;
14821  }
14822 
14823  //
14824  // Process "integrated codelet FFT" operation
14825  //
14826  if( operation==opcomplexcodelettwfft )
14827  {
14828  ftapplycomplexcodelettwfft(a, abase+aoffset, operandscnt, operandsize, microvectorsize, _params);
14829  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14830  continue;
14831  }
14832 
14833  //
14834  // Process Bluestein's FFT operation
14835  //
14836  if( operation==opbluesteinsfft )
14837  {
14838  alglib.ap.assert(microvectorsize==2, "FTApplySubPlan: microvectorsize!=2 for Bluesteins FFT");
14839  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_retrieve(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufa);
14840  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_retrieve(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufb);
14841  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_retrieve(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufc);
14842  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_retrieve(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufd);
14843  ftbluesteinsfft(plan, a, abase, aoffset, operandscnt, operandsize, plan.entries[rowidx,colparam0], plan.entries[rowidx,colparam2], rowidx+plan.entries[rowidx,colparam1], bufa.val, bufb.val, bufc.val, bufd.val, _params);
14844  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_recycle(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufa);
14845  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_recycle(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufb);
14846  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_recycle(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufc);
14847  alglib.smp.ae_shared_pool_recycle(plan.bluesteinpool, ref bufd);
14848  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14849  continue;
14850  }
14851 
14852  //
14853  // Process Rader's FFT
14854  //
14855  if( operation==opradersfft )
14856  {
14857  ftradersfft(plan, a, abase, aoffset, operandscnt, operandsize, rowidx+plan.entries[rowidx,colparam0], plan.entries[rowidx,colparam1], plan.entries[rowidx,colparam2], plan.entries[rowidx,colparam3], buf, _params);
14858  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14859  continue;
14860  }
14861 
14862  //
14863  // Process "complex twiddle factors" operation
14864  //
14865  if( operation==opcomplexfftfactors )
14866  {
14867  alglib.ap.assert(microvectorsize==2, "FTApplySubPlan: MicrovectorSize<>1");
14868  n1 = plan.entries[rowidx,colparam0];
14869  n2 = operandsize/n1;
14870  for(i=0; i<=operandscnt-1; i++)
14871  {
14872  ffttwcalc(a, abase+aoffset+i*operandsize*2, n1, n2, _params);
14873  }
14874  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14875  continue;
14876  }
14877 
14878  //
14879  // Process "complex transposition" operation
14880  //
14881  if( operation==opcomplextranspose )
14882  {
14883  alglib.ap.assert(microvectorsize==2, "FTApplySubPlan: MicrovectorSize<>1");
14884  n1 = plan.entries[rowidx,colparam0];
14885  n2 = operandsize/n1;
14886  for(i=0; i<=operandscnt-1; i++)
14887  {
14888  internalcomplexlintranspose(a, n1, n2, abase+aoffset+i*operandsize*2, buf, _params);
14889  }
14890  rowidx = rowidx+1;
14891  continue;
14892  }
14893 
14894  //
14895  // Error
14896  //
14897  alglib.ap.assert(false, "FTApplySubPlan: unexpected plan type");
14898  }
14899  }
14900 
14901 
14902  /*************************************************************************
14903  This subroutine applies complex reference FFT to input/output array A.
14904 
14905  VERY SLOW OPERATION, do not use it in real life plans :)
14906 
14907  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14908  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
14909  Offs - offset of the subarray to process
14910  OperandsCnt - operands count (see description of FastTransformPlan)
14911  OperandSize - operand size (see description of FastTransformPlan)
14912  MicrovectorSize-microvector size (see description of FastTransformPlan)
14913  Buf - temporary array, must be at least OperandsCnt*OperandSize*MicrovectorSize
14914 
14915  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14916  A - transformed array
14917 
14918  -- ALGLIB --
14919  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14920  *************************************************************************/
14921  private static void ftapplycomplexreffft(double[] a,
14922  int offs,
14923  int operandscnt,
14924  int operandsize,
14925  int microvectorsize,
14926  double[] buf,
14927  alglib.xparams _params)
14928  {
14929  int opidx = 0;
14930  int i = 0;
14931  int k = 0;
14932  double hre = 0;
14933  double him = 0;
14934  double c = 0;
14935  double s = 0;
14936  double re = 0;
14937  double im = 0;
14938  int n = 0;
14939 
14940  alglib.ap.assert(operandscnt>=1, "FTApplyComplexRefFFT: OperandsCnt<1");
14941  alglib.ap.assert(operandsize>=1, "FTApplyComplexRefFFT: OperandSize<1");
14942  alglib.ap.assert(microvectorsize==2, "FTApplyComplexRefFFT: MicrovectorSize<>2");
14943  n = operandsize;
14944  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
14945  {
14946  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
14947  {
14948  hre = 0;
14949  him = 0;
14950  for(k=0; k<=n-1; k++)
14951  {
14952  re = a[offs+opidx*operandsize*2+2*k+0];
14953  im = a[offs+opidx*operandsize*2+2*k+1];
14954  c = Math.Cos(-(2*Math.PI*k*i/n));
14955  s = Math.Sin(-(2*Math.PI*k*i/n));
14956  hre = hre+c*re-s*im;
14957  him = him+c*im+s*re;
14958  }
14959  buf[2*i+0] = hre;
14960  buf[2*i+1] = him;
14961  }
14962  for(i=0; i<=operandsize*2-1; i++)
14963  {
14964  a[offs+opidx*operandsize*2+i] = buf[i];
14965  }
14966  }
14967  }
14968 
14969 
14970  /*************************************************************************
14971  This subroutine applies complex codelet FFT to input/output array A.
14972 
14973  INPUT PARAMETERS:
14974  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
14975  Offs - offset of the subarray to process
14976  OperandsCnt - operands count (see description of FastTransformPlan)
14977  OperandSize - operand size (see description of FastTransformPlan)
14978  MicrovectorSize-microvector size, must be 2
14979 
14980  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
14981  A - transformed array
14982 
14983  -- ALGLIB --
14984  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
14985  *************************************************************************/
14986  private static void ftapplycomplexcodeletfft(double[] a,
14987  int offs,
14988  int operandscnt,
14989  int operandsize,
14990  int microvectorsize,
14991  alglib.xparams _params)
14992  {
14993  int opidx = 0;
14994  int n = 0;
14995  int aoffset = 0;
14996  double a0x = 0;
14997  double a0y = 0;
14998  double a1x = 0;
14999  double a1y = 0;
15000  double a2x = 0;
15001  double a2y = 0;
15002  double a3x = 0;
15003  double a3y = 0;
15004  double a4x = 0;
15005  double a4y = 0;
15006  double a5x = 0;
15007  double a5y = 0;
15008  double v0 = 0;
15009  double v1 = 0;
15010  double v2 = 0;
15011  double v3 = 0;
15012  double t1x = 0;
15013  double t1y = 0;
15014  double t2x = 0;
15015  double t2y = 0;
15016  double t3x = 0;
15017  double t3y = 0;
15018  double t4x = 0;
15019  double t4y = 0;
15020  double t5x = 0;
15021  double t5y = 0;
15022  double m1x = 0;
15023  double m1y = 0;
15024  double m2x = 0;
15025  double m2y = 0;
15026  double m3x = 0;
15027  double m3y = 0;
15028  double m4x = 0;
15029  double m4y = 0;
15030  double m5x = 0;
15031  double m5y = 0;
15032  double s1x = 0;
15033  double s1y = 0;
15034  double s2x = 0;
15035  double s2y = 0;
15036  double s3x = 0;
15037  double s3y = 0;
15038  double s4x = 0;
15039  double s4y = 0;
15040  double s5x = 0;
15041  double s5y = 0;
15042  double c1 = 0;
15043  double c2 = 0;
15044  double c3 = 0;
15045  double c4 = 0;
15046  double c5 = 0;
15047  double v = 0;
15048 
15049  alglib.ap.assert(operandscnt>=1, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: OperandsCnt<1");
15050  alglib.ap.assert(operandsize>=1, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: OperandSize<1");
15051  alglib.ap.assert(microvectorsize==2, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: MicrovectorSize<>2");
15052  n = operandsize;
15053 
15054  //
15055  // Hard-coded transforms for different N's
15056  //
15057  alglib.ap.assert(n<=maxradix, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: N>MaxRadix");
15058  if( n==2 )
15059  {
15060  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
15061  {
15062  aoffset = offs+opidx*operandsize*2;
15063  a0x = a[aoffset+0];
15064  a0y = a[aoffset+1];
15065  a1x = a[aoffset+2];
15066  a1y = a[aoffset+3];
15067  v0 = a0x+a1x;
15068  v1 = a0y+a1y;
15069  v2 = a0x-a1x;
15070  v3 = a0y-a1y;
15071  a[aoffset+0] = v0;
15072  a[aoffset+1] = v1;
15073  a[aoffset+2] = v2;
15074  a[aoffset+3] = v3;
15075  }
15076  return;
15077  }
15078  if( n==3 )
15079  {
15080  c1 = Math.Cos(2*Math.PI/3)-1;
15081  c2 = Math.Sin(2*Math.PI/3);
15082  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
15083  {
15084  aoffset = offs+opidx*operandsize*2;
15085  a0x = a[aoffset+0];
15086  a0y = a[aoffset+1];
15087  a1x = a[aoffset+2];
15088  a1y = a[aoffset+3];
15089  a2x = a[aoffset+4];
15090  a2y = a[aoffset+5];
15091  t1x = a1x+a2x;
15092  t1y = a1y+a2y;
15093  a0x = a0x+t1x;
15094  a0y = a0y+t1y;
15095  m1x = c1*t1x;
15096  m1y = c1*t1y;
15097  m2x = c2*(a1y-a2y);
15098  m2y = c2*(a2x-a1x);
15099  s1x = a0x+m1x;
15100  s1y = a0y+m1y;
15101  a1x = s1x+m2x;
15102  a1y = s1y+m2y;
15103  a2x = s1x-m2x;
15104  a2y = s1y-m2y;
15105  a[aoffset+0] = a0x;
15106  a[aoffset+1] = a0y;
15107  a[aoffset+2] = a1x;
15108  a[aoffset+3] = a1y;
15109  a[aoffset+4] = a2x;
15110  a[aoffset+5] = a2y;
15111  }
15112  return;
15113  }
15114  if( n==4 )
15115  {
15116  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
15117  {
15118  aoffset = offs+opidx*operandsize*2;
15119  a0x = a[aoffset+0];
15120  a0y = a[aoffset+1];
15121  a1x = a[aoffset+2];
15122  a1y = a[aoffset+3];
15123  a2x = a[aoffset+4];
15124  a2y = a[aoffset+5];
15125  a3x = a[aoffset+6];
15126  a3y = a[aoffset+7];
15127  t1x = a0x+a2x;
15128  t1y = a0y+a2y;
15129  t2x = a1x+a3x;
15130  t2y = a1y+a3y;
15131  m2x = a0x-a2x;
15132  m2y = a0y-a2y;
15133  m3x = a1y-a3y;
15134  m3y = a3x-a1x;
15135  a[aoffset+0] = t1x+t2x;
15136  a[aoffset+1] = t1y+t2y;
15137  a[aoffset+4] = t1x-t2x;
15138  a[aoffset+5] = t1y-t2y;
15139  a[aoffset+2] = m2x+m3x;
15140  a[aoffset+3] = m2y+m3y;
15141  a[aoffset+6] = m2x-m3x;
15142  a[aoffset+7] = m2y-m3y;
15143  }
15144  return;
15145  }
15146  if( n==5 )
15147  {
15148  v = 2*Math.PI/5;
15149  c1 = (Math.Cos(v)+Math.Cos(2*v))/2-1;
15150  c2 = (Math.Cos(v)-Math.Cos(2*v))/2;
15151  c3 = -Math.Sin(v);
15152  c4 = -(Math.Sin(v)+Math.Sin(2*v));
15153  c5 = Math.Sin(v)-Math.Sin(2*v);
15154  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
15155  {
15156  aoffset = offs+opidx*operandsize*2;
15157  t1x = a[aoffset+2]+a[aoffset+8];
15158  t1y = a[aoffset+3]+a[aoffset+9];
15159  t2x = a[aoffset+4]+a[aoffset+6];
15160  t2y = a[aoffset+5]+a[aoffset+7];
15161  t3x = a[aoffset+2]-a[aoffset+8];
15162  t3y = a[aoffset+3]-a[aoffset+9];
15163  t4x = a[aoffset+6]-a[aoffset+4];
15164  t4y = a[aoffset+7]-a[aoffset+5];
15165  t5x = t1x+t2x;
15166  t5y = t1y+t2y;
15167  a[aoffset+0] = a[aoffset+0]+t5x;
15168  a[aoffset+1] = a[aoffset+1]+t5y;
15169  m1x = c1*t5x;
15170  m1y = c1*t5y;
15171  m2x = c2*(t1x-t2x);
15172  m2y = c2*(t1y-t2y);
15173  m3x = -(c3*(t3y+t4y));
15174  m3y = c3*(t3x+t4x);
15175  m4x = -(c4*t4y);
15176  m4y = c4*t4x;
15177  m5x = -(c5*t3y);
15178  m5y = c5*t3x;
15179  s3x = m3x-m4x;
15180  s3y = m3y-m4y;
15181  s5x = m3x+m5x;
15182  s5y = m3y+m5y;
15183  s1x = a[aoffset+0]+m1x;
15184  s1y = a[aoffset+1]+m1y;
15185  s2x = s1x+m2x;
15186  s2y = s1y+m2y;
15187  s4x = s1x-m2x;
15188  s4y = s1y-m2y;
15189  a[aoffset+2] = s2x+s3x;
15190  a[aoffset+3] = s2y+s3y;
15191  a[aoffset+4] = s4x+s5x;
15192  a[aoffset+5] = s4y+s5y;
15193  a[aoffset+6] = s4x-s5x;
15194  a[aoffset+7] = s4y-s5y;
15195  a[aoffset+8] = s2x-s3x;
15196  a[aoffset+9] = s2y-s3y;
15197  }
15198  return;
15199  }
15200  if( n==6 )
15201  {
15202  c1 = Math.Cos(2*Math.PI/3)-1;
15203  c2 = Math.Sin(2*Math.PI/3);
15204  c3 = Math.Cos(-(Math.PI/3));
15205  c4 = Math.Sin(-(Math.PI/3));
15206  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
15207  {
15208  aoffset = offs+opidx*operandsize*2;
15209  a0x = a[aoffset+0];
15210  a0y = a[aoffset+1];
15211  a1x = a[aoffset+2];
15212  a1y = a[aoffset+3];
15213  a2x = a[aoffset+4];
15214  a2y = a[aoffset+5];
15215  a3x = a[aoffset+6];
15216  a3y = a[aoffset+7];
15217  a4x = a[aoffset+8];
15218  a4y = a[aoffset+9];
15219  a5x = a[aoffset+10];
15220  a5y = a[aoffset+11];
15221  v0 = a0x;
15222  v1 = a0y;
15223  a0x = a0x+a3x;
15224  a0y = a0y+a3y;
15225  a3x = v0-a3x;
15226  a3y = v1-a3y;
15227  v0 = a1x;
15228  v1 = a1y;
15229  a1x = a1x+a4x;
15230  a1y = a1y+a4y;
15231  a4x = v0-a4x;
15232  a4y = v1-a4y;
15233  v0 = a2x;
15234  v1 = a2y;
15235  a2x = a2x+a5x;
15236  a2y = a2y+a5y;
15237  a5x = v0-a5x;
15238  a5y = v1-a5y;
15239  t4x = a4x*c3-a4y*c4;
15240  t4y = a4x*c4+a4y*c3;
15241  a4x = t4x;
15242  a4y = t4y;
15243  t5x = -(a5x*c3)-a5y*c4;
15244  t5y = a5x*c4-a5y*c3;
15245  a5x = t5x;
15246  a5y = t5y;
15247  t1x = a1x+a2x;
15248  t1y = a1y+a2y;
15249  a0x = a0x+t1x;
15250  a0y = a0y+t1y;
15251  m1x = c1*t1x;
15252  m1y = c1*t1y;
15253  m2x = c2*(a1y-a2y);
15254  m2y = c2*(a2x-a1x);
15255  s1x = a0x+m1x;
15256  s1y = a0y+m1y;
15257  a1x = s1x+m2x;
15258  a1y = s1y+m2y;
15259  a2x = s1x-m2x;
15260  a2y = s1y-m2y;
15261  t1x = a4x+a5x;
15262  t1y = a4y+a5y;
15263  a3x = a3x+t1x;
15264  a3y = a3y+t1y;
15265  m1x = c1*t1x;
15266  m1y = c1*t1y;
15267  m2x = c2*(a4y-a5y);
15268  m2y = c2*(a5x-a4x);
15269  s1x = a3x+m1x;
15270  s1y = a3y+m1y;
15271  a4x = s1x+m2x;
15272  a4y = s1y+m2y;
15273  a5x = s1x-m2x;
15274  a5y = s1y-m2y;
15275  a[aoffset+0] = a0x;
15276  a[aoffset+1] = a0y;
15277  a[aoffset+2] = a3x;
15278  a[aoffset+3] = a3y;
15279  a[aoffset+4] = a1x;
15280  a[aoffset+5] = a1y;
15281  a[aoffset+6] = a4x;
15282  a[aoffset+7] = a4y;
15283  a[aoffset+8] = a2x;
15284  a[aoffset+9] = a2y;
15285  a[aoffset+10] = a5x;
15286  a[aoffset+11] = a5y;
15287  }
15288  return;
15289  }
15290  }
15291 
15292 
15293  /*************************************************************************
15294  This subroutine applies complex "integrated" codelet FFT to input/output
15295  array A. "Integrated" codelet differs from "normal" one in following ways:
15296  * it can work with MicrovectorSize>1
15297  * hence, it can be used in Cooley-Tukey FFT without transpositions
15298  * it performs inlined multiplication by twiddle factors of Cooley-Tukey
15299  FFT with N2=MicrovectorSize/2.
15300 
15301  INPUT PARAMETERS:
15302  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
15303  Offs - offset of the subarray to process
15304  OperandsCnt - operands count (see description of FastTransformPlan)
15305  OperandSize - operand size (see description of FastTransformPlan)
15306  MicrovectorSize-microvector size, must be 1
15307 
15308  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
15309  A - transformed array
15310 
15311  -- ALGLIB --
15312  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
15313  *************************************************************************/
15314  private static void ftapplycomplexcodelettwfft(double[] a,
15315  int offs,
15316  int operandscnt,
15317  int operandsize,
15318  int microvectorsize,
15319  alglib.xparams _params)
15320  {
15321  int opidx = 0;
15322  int mvidx = 0;

15324  int m = 0;
15325  int aoffset0 = 0;

15364  double m3y = 0;

15374  double s3y = 0;
15375  double s4x = 0;
15376  double s4y = 0;
15377  double s5x = 0;
15378  double s5y = 0;
15379  double c1 = 0;
15380  double c2 = 0;
15381  double c3 = 0;
15382  double c4 = 0;
15383  double c5 = 0;

15387  double twx = 0;

15399  alglib.ap.assert(operandscnt>=1, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: OperandsCnt<1");
15400  alglib.ap.assert(operandsize>=1, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: OperandSize<1");

15402  alglib.ap.assert(microvectorsize%2==0, "FTApplyComplexCodeletFFT: MicrovectorSize is not even");
15403  n = operandsize;
15404  m = microvectorsize/2;
15405 
15406  //
15407  // Hard-coded transforms for different N's
15408  //
15409  alglib.ap.assert(n<=maxradix, "FTApplyComplexCodeletTwFFT: N>MaxRadix");
15410  if( n==2 )
15411  {
15412  v = -(2*Math.PI/(n*m));
15413  tw0 = -(2*math.sqr(Math.Sin(0.5*v)));
15414  tw1 = Math.Sin(v);
15415  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
15416  {
15417  aoffset0 = offs+opidx*operandsize*microvectorsize;
15418  aoffset2 = aoffset0+microvectorsize;
15419  twxm1 = 0.0;
15420  twy = 0.0;
15421  for(mvidx=0; mvidx<=m-1; mvidx++)
15422  {
15423  a0x = a[aoffset0];
15424  a0y = a[aoffset0+1];
15425  a1x = a[aoffset2];
15426  a1y = a[aoffset2+1];
15427  v0 = a0x+a1x;
15428  v1 = a0y+a1y;
15429  v2 = a0x-a1x;
15430  v3 = a0y-a1y;
15431  a[aoffset0] = v0;
15432  a[aoffset0+1] = v1;
15433  a[aoffset2] = v2*(1+twxm1)-v3*twy;
15434  a[aoffset2+1] = v3*(1+twxm1)+v2*twy;
15435  aoffset0 = aoffset0+2;
15436  aoffset2 = aoffset2+2;
15437  if( (mvidx+1)%updatetw==0 )
15438  {
15439  v = -(2*Math.PI*(mvidx+1)/(n*m));
15440  twxm1 = Math.Sin(0.5*v);
15441  twxm1 = -(2*twxm1*twxm1);
15442  twy = Math.Sin(v);
15443  }
15444  else
15445  {
15446  v = twxm1+tw0+twxm1*tw0-twy*tw1;
15447  twy = twy+tw1+twxm1*tw1+twy*tw0;
15448  twxm1 = v;
15449  }
15450  }
15451  }
15452  return;

15482  m1y = c1*t1y;

15497  a[aoffset4] = a2x*tw2x-a2y*tw2y;
15498  a[aoffset4+1] = a2y*tw2x+a2x*tw2y;

15500  aoffset2 = aoffset2+2;
15501  aoffset4 = aoffset4+2;

15503  {

15505  twxm1 = Math.Sin(0.5*v);
15506  twxm1 = -(2*twxm1*twxm1);
15507  twy = Math.Sin(v);
15508  twx = twxm1+1;
15509  }
15510  else
15511  {
15512  v = twxm1+tw0+twxm1*tw0-twy*tw1;
15513  twy = twy+tw1+twxm1*tw1+twy*tw0;
15514  twxm1 = v;
15515  twx = v+1;
15516  }
15517  }
15518  }
15519  return;

15579  twxm1 = -(2*twxm1*twxm1);
15580  twy = Math.Sin(v);
15581  twx = twxm1+1;
15582  }
15583  else

15598  tw1 = Math.Sin(v);
15599  v = 2*Math.PI/5;
15600  c1 = (Math.Cos(v)+Math.Cos(2*v))/2-1;
