15790  s1y = a3y+m1y;
15791  a4x = s1x+m2x;
15792  a4y = s1y+m2y;
15793  a5x = s1x-m2x;
15794  a5y = s1y-m2y;
15795  tw2x = twx*twx-twy*twy;
15796  tw2y = 2*twx*twy;
15797  tw3x = twx*tw2x-twy*tw2y;
15798  tw3y = twx*tw2y+twy*tw2x;
15799  tw4x = tw2x*tw2x-tw2y*tw2y;
15800  tw4y = 2*tw2x*tw2y;
15801  tw5x = tw3x*tw2x-tw3y*tw2y;
15802  tw5y = tw3x*tw2y+tw3y*tw2x;
15803  a[aoffset0+0] = a0x;
15804  a[aoffset0+1] = a0y;
15805  a[aoffset2+0] = a3x*twx-a3y*twy;
15806  a[aoffset2+1] = a3y*twx+a3x*twy;
15807  a[aoffset4+0] = a1x*tw2x-a1y*tw2y;
15808  a[aoffset4+1] = a1y*tw2x+a1x*tw2y;
15809  a[aoffset6+0] = a4x*tw3x-a4y*tw3y;
15810  a[aoffset6+1] = a4y*tw3x+a4x*tw3y;
15811  a[aoffset8+0] = a2x*tw4x-a2y*tw4y;
15812  a[aoffset8+1] = a2y*tw4x+a2x*tw4y;
15813  a[aoffset10+0] = a5x*tw5x-a5y*tw5y;
15814  a[aoffset10+1] = a5y*tw5x+a5x*tw5y;
15815  aoffset0 = aoffset0+2;
15816  aoffset2 = aoffset2+2;
15817  aoffset4 = aoffset4+2;
15818  aoffset6 = aoffset6+2;
15819  aoffset8 = aoffset8+2;
15820  aoffset10 = aoffset10+2;
15821  if( (mvidx+1)%updatetw==0 )
15822  {
15823  v = -(2*Math.PI*(mvidx+1)/(n*m));
15824  twxm1 = Math.Sin(0.5*v);
15825  twxm1 = -(2*twxm1*twxm1);
15826  twy = Math.Sin(v);
15827  twx = twxm1+1;
15828  }
15829  else
15830  {
15831  v = twxm1+tw0+twxm1*tw0-twy*tw1;
15832  twy = twy+tw1+twxm1*tw1+twy*tw0;
15833  twxm1 = v;
15834  twx = v+1;
15835  }
15836  }
15837  }
15838  return;
15839  }
15840  }
15841 
15842 
15843  /*************************************************************************
15844  This subroutine precomputes data for complex Bluestein's FFT and writes
15845  them to array PrecR[] at specified offset. It is responsibility of the
15846  caller to make sure that PrecR[] is large enough.
15847 
15848  INPUT PARAMETERS:
15849  N - original size of the transform
15850  M - size of the "padded" Bluestein's transform
15851  PrecR - preallocated array
15852  Offs - offset
15853 
15854  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
15855  PrecR - data at Offs:Offs+4*M-1 are modified:
15856  * PrecR[Offs:Offs+2*M-1] stores Z[k]=exp(i*pi*k^2/N)
15857  * PrecR[Offs+2*M:Offs+4*M-1] stores FFT of the Z
15858  Other parts of PrecR are unchanged.
15859 
15860  NOTE: this function performs internal M-point FFT. It allocates temporary
15861  plan which is destroyed after leaving this function.
15862 
15863  -- ALGLIB --
15864  Copyright 08.05.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
15865  *************************************************************************/
15866  private static void ftprecomputebluesteinsfft(int n,
15867  int m,
15868  double[] precr,
15869  int offs,
15870  alglib.xparams _params)
15871  {
15872  int i = 0;
15873  double bx = 0;
15874  double by = 0;
15875  fasttransformplan plan = new fasttransformplan();
15876 
15877 
15878  //
15879  // Fill first half of PrecR with b[k] = exp(i*pi*k^2/N)
15880  //
15881  for(i=0; i<=2*m-1; i++)
15882  {
15883  precr[offs+i] = 0;
15884  }
15885  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
15886  {
15887  bx = Math.Cos(Math.PI/n*i*i);
15888  by = Math.Sin(Math.PI/n*i*i);
15889  precr[offs+2*i+0] = bx;
15890  precr[offs+2*i+1] = by;
15891  precr[offs+2*((m-i)%m)+0] = bx;
15892  precr[offs+2*((m-i)%m)+1] = by;
15893  }
15894 
15895  //
15896  // Precomputed FFT
15897  //
15898  ftcomplexfftplan(m, 1, plan, _params);
15899  for(i=0; i<=2*m-1; i++)
15900  {
15901  precr[offs+2*m+i] = precr[offs+i];
15902  }
15903  ftapplysubplan(plan, 0, precr, offs+2*m, 0, plan.buffer, 1, _params);
15904  }
15905 
15906 
15907  /*************************************************************************
15908  This subroutine applies complex Bluestein's FFT to input/output array A.
15909 
15910  INPUT PARAMETERS:
15911  Plan - transformation plan
15912  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
15913  ABase - base offset in array A, this value points to start of
15914  subarray whose length is equal to length of the plan
15915  AOffset - offset with respect to ABase, 0<=AOffset<PlanLength.
15916  This is an offset within large PlanLength-subarray of
15917  the chunk to process.
15918  OperandsCnt - number of repeated operands (length N each)
15919  N - original data length (measured in complex numbers)
15920  M - padded data length (measured in complex numbers)
15921  PrecOffs - offset of the precomputed data for the plan
15922  SubPlan - position of the length-M FFT subplan which is used by
15923  transformation
15924  BufA - temporary buffer, at least 2*M elements
15925  BufB - temporary buffer, at least 2*M elements
15926  BufC - temporary buffer, at least 2*M elements
15927  BufD - temporary buffer, at least 2*M elements
15928 
15929  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
15930  A - transformed array
15931 
15932  -- ALGLIB --
15933  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
15934  *************************************************************************/
15935  private static void ftbluesteinsfft(fasttransformplan plan,
15936  double[] a,
15937  int abase,
15938  int aoffset,
15939  int operandscnt,
15940  int n,
15941  int m,
15942  int precoffs,
15943  int subplan,
15944  double[] bufa,
15945  double[] bufb,
15946  double[] bufc,
15947  double[] bufd,
15948  alglib.xparams _params)
15949  {
15950  int op = 0;
15951  int i = 0;
15952  double x = 0;
15953  double y = 0;
15954  double bx = 0;
15955  double by = 0;
15956  double ax = 0;
15957  double ay = 0;
15958  double rx = 0;
15959  double ry = 0;
15960  int p0 = 0;
15961  int p1 = 0;
15962  int p2 = 0;
15963 
15964  for(op=0; op<=operandscnt-1; op++)
15965  {
15966 
15967  //
15968  // Multiply A by conj(Z), store to buffer.
15969  // Pad A by zeros.
15970  //
15971  // NOTE: Z[k]=exp(i*pi*k^2/N)
15972  //
15973  p0 = abase+aoffset+op*2*n;
15974  p1 = precoffs;
15975  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
15976  {
15977  x = a[p0+0];
15978  y = a[p0+1];
15979  bx = plan.precr[p1+0];
15980  by = -plan.precr[p1+1];
15981  bufa[2*i+0] = x*bx-y*by;
15982  bufa[2*i+1] = x*by+y*bx;
15983  p0 = p0+2;
15984  p1 = p1+2;
15985  }
15986  for(i=2*n; i<=2*m-1; i++)
15987  {
15988  bufa[i] = 0;
15989  }
15990 
15991  //
15992  // Perform convolution of A and Z (using precomputed
15993  // FFT of Z stored in Plan structure).
15994  //
15995  ftapplysubplan(plan, subplan, bufa, 0, 0, bufc, 1, _params);
15996  p0 = 0;
15997  p1 = precoffs+2*m;
15998  for(i=0; i<=m-1; i++)
15999  {
16000  ax = bufa[p0+0];
16001  ay = bufa[p0+1];
16002  bx = plan.precr[p1+0];
16003  by = plan.precr[p1+1];
16004  bufa[p0+0] = ax*bx-ay*by;
16005  bufa[p0+1] = -(ax*by+ay*bx);
16006  p0 = p0+2;
16007  p1 = p1+2;
16008  }
16009  ftapplysubplan(plan, subplan, bufa, 0, 0, bufc, 1, _params);
16010 
16011  //
16012  // Post processing:
16013  // A:=conj(Z)*conj(A)/M
16014  // Here conj(A)/M corresponds to last stage of inverse DFT,
16015  // and conj(Z) comes from Bluestein's FFT algorithm.
16016  //
16017  p0 = precoffs;
16018  p1 = 0;
16019  p2 = abase+aoffset+op*2*n;
16020  for(i=0; i<=n-1; i++)
16021  {
16022  bx = plan.precr[p0+0];
16023  by = plan.precr[p0+1];
16024  rx = bufa[p1+0]/m;
16025  ry = -(bufa[p1+1]/m);
16026  a[p2+0] = rx*bx-ry*-by;
16027  a[p2+1] = rx*-by+ry*bx;
16028  p0 = p0+2;
16029  p1 = p1+2;
16030  p2 = p2+2;
16031  }
16032  }
16033  }
16034 
16035 
16036  /*************************************************************************
16037  This subroutine precomputes data for complex Rader's FFT and writes them
16038  to array PrecR[] at specified offset. It is responsibility of the caller
16039  to make sure that PrecR[] is large enough.
16040 
16041  INPUT PARAMETERS:
16042  N - original size of the transform (before reduction to N-1)
16043  RQ - primitive root modulo N
16044  RIQ - inverse of primitive root modulo N
16045  PrecR - preallocated array
16046  Offs - offset
16047 
16048  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
16049  PrecR - data at Offs:Offs+2*(N-1)-1 store FFT of Rader's factors,
16050  other parts of PrecR are unchanged.
16051 
16052  NOTE: this function performs internal (N-1)-point FFT. It allocates temporary
16053  plan which is destroyed after leaving this function.
16054 
16055  -- ALGLIB --
16056  Copyright 08.05.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
16057  *************************************************************************/
16058  private static void ftprecomputeradersfft(int n,
16059  int rq,
16060  int riq,
16061  double[] precr,
16062  int offs,
16063  alglib.xparams _params)
16064  {
16065  int q = 0;
16066  fasttransformplan plan = new fasttransformplan();
16067  int kiq = 0;
16068  double v = 0;
16069 
16070 
16071  //
16072  // Fill PrecR with Rader factors, perform FFT
16073  //
16074  kiq = 1;
16075  for(q=0; q<=n-2; q++)
16076  {
16077  v = -(2*Math.PI*kiq/n);
16078  precr[offs+2*q+0] = Math.Cos(v);
16079  precr[offs+2*q+1] = Math.Sin(v);
16080  kiq = kiq*riq%n;
16081  }
16082  ftcomplexfftplan(n-1, 1, plan, _params);
16083  ftapplysubplan(plan, 0, precr, offs, 0, plan.buffer, 1, _params);
16084  }
16085 
16086 
16087  /*************************************************************************
16088  This subroutine applies complex Rader's FFT to input/output array A.
16089 
16090  INPUT PARAMETERS:
16091  A - array, must be large enough for plan to work
16092  ABase - base offset in array A, this value points to start of
16093  subarray whose length is equal to length of the plan
16094  AOffset - offset with respect to ABase, 0<=AOffset<PlanLength.
16095  This is an offset within large PlanLength-subarray of
16096  the chunk to process.
16097  OperandsCnt - number of repeated operands (length N each)
16098  N - original data length (measured in complex numbers)
16099  SubPlan - position of the (N-1)-point FFT subplan which is used
16100  by transformation
16101  RQ - primitive root modulo N
16102  RIQ - inverse of primitive root modulo N
16103  PrecOffs - offset of the precomputed data for the plan
16104  Buf - temporary array
16105 
16106  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
16107  A - transformed array
16108 
16109  -- ALGLIB --
16110  Copyright 05.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
16111  *************************************************************************/
16112  private static void ftradersfft(fasttransformplan plan,
16113  double[] a,
16114  int abase,
16115  int aoffset,
16116  int operandscnt,
16117  int n,
16118  int subplan,
16119  int rq,
16120  int riq,
16121  int precoffs,
16122  double[] buf,
16123  alglib.xparams _params)
16124  {
16125  int opidx = 0;
16126  int i = 0;
16127  int q = 0;
16128  int kq = 0;
16129  int kiq = 0;
16130  double x0 = 0;
16131  double y0 = 0;
16132  int p0 = 0;
16133  int p1 = 0;
16134  double ax = 0;
16135  double ay = 0;
16136  double bx = 0;
16137  double by = 0;
16138  double rx = 0;
16139  double ry = 0;
16140 
16141  alglib.ap.assert(operandscnt>=1, "FTApplyComplexRefFFT: OperandsCnt<1");
16142 
16143  //
16144  // Process operands
16145  //
16146  for(opidx=0; opidx<=operandscnt-1; opidx++)
16147  {
16148 
16149  //
16150  // fill QA
16151  //
16152  kq = 1;
16153  p0 = abase+aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16154  p1 = aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16155  rx = a[p0+0];
16156  ry = a[p0+1];
16157  x0 = rx;
16158  y0 = ry;
16159  for(q=0; q<=n-2; q++)
16160  {
16161  ax = a[p0+2*kq+0];
16162  ay = a[p0+2*kq+1];
16163  buf[p1+0] = ax;
16164  buf[p1+1] = ay;
16165  rx = rx+ax;
16166  ry = ry+ay;
16167  kq = kq*rq%n;
16168  p1 = p1+2;
16169  }
16170  p0 = abase+aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16171  p1 = aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16172  for(q=0; q<=n-2; q++)
16173  {
16174  a[p0] = buf[p1];
16175  a[p0+1] = buf[p1+1];
16176  p0 = p0+2;
16177  p1 = p1+2;
16178  }
16179 
16180  //
16181  // Convolution
16182  //
16183  ftapplysubplan(plan, subplan, a, abase, aoffset+opidx*n*2, buf, 1, _params);
16184  p0 = abase+aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16185  p1 = precoffs;
16186  for(i=0; i<=n-2; i++)
16187  {
16188  ax = a[p0+0];
16189  ay = a[p0+1];
16190  bx = plan.precr[p1+0];
16191  by = plan.precr[p1+1];
16192  a[p0+0] = ax*bx-ay*by;
16193  a[p0+1] = -(ax*by+ay*bx);
16194  p0 = p0+2;
16195  p1 = p1+2;
16196  }
16197  ftapplysubplan(plan, subplan, a, abase, aoffset+opidx*n*2, buf, 1, _params);
16198  p0 = abase+aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16199  for(i=0; i<=n-2; i++)
16200  {
16201  a[p0+0] = a[p0+0]/(n-1);
16202  a[p0+1] = -(a[p0+1]/(n-1));
16203  p0 = p0+2;
16204  }
16205 
16206  //
16207  // Result
16208  //
16209  buf[aoffset+opidx*n*2+0] = rx;
16210  buf[aoffset+opidx*n*2+1] = ry;
16211  kiq = 1;
16212  p0 = aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16213  p1 = abase+aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16214  for(q=0; q<=n-2; q++)
16215  {
16216  buf[p0+2*kiq+0] = x0+a[p1+0];
16217  buf[p0+2*kiq+1] = y0+a[p1+1];
16218  kiq = kiq*riq%n;
16219  p1 = p1+2;
16220  }
16221  p0 = abase+aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16222  p1 = aoffset+opidx*n*2;
16223  for(q=0; q<=n-1; q++)
16224  {
16225  a[p0] = buf[p1];
16226  a[p0+1] = buf[p1+1];
16227  p0 = p0+2;
16228  p1 = p1+2;
16229  }
16230  }
16231  }
16232 
16233 
16234  /*************************************************************************
16235  Factorizes task size N into product of two smaller sizes N1 and N2
16236 
16237  INPUT PARAMETERS:
16238  N - task size, N>0
16239  IsRoot - whether taks is root task (first one in a sequence)
16240 
16241  OUTPUT PARAMETERS:
16242  N1, N2 - such numbers that:
16243  * for prime N: N1=N2=0
16244  * for composite N<=MaxRadix: N1=N2=0
16245  * for composite N>MaxRadix: 1<=N1<=N2, N1*N2=N
16246 
16247  -- ALGLIB --
16248  Copyright 08.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
16249  *************************************************************************/
16250  private static void ftfactorize(int n,
16251  bool isroot,
16252  ref int n1,
16253  ref int n2,
16254  alglib.xparams _params)
16255  {
16256  int j = 0;
16257  int k = 0;
16258 
16259  n1 = 0;
16260  n2 = 0;
16261 
16262  alglib.ap.assert(n>0, "FTFactorize: N<=0");
16263  n1 = 0;
16264  n2 = 0;
16265 
16266  //
16267  // Small N
16268  //
16269  if( n<=maxradix )
16270  {
16271  return;
16272  }
16273 
16274  //
16275  // Large N, recursive split
16276  //
16277  if( n>recursivethreshold )
16278  {
16279  k = (int)Math.Ceiling(Math.Sqrt(n))+1;
16280  alglib.ap.assert(k*k>=n, "FTFactorize: internal error during recursive factorization");
16281  for(j=k; j>=2; j--)
16282  {
16283  if( n%j==0 )
16284  {
16285  n1 = Math.Min(n/j, j);
16286  n2 = Math.Max(n/j, j);
16287  return;
16288  }
16289  }
16290  }
16291 
16292  //
16293  // N>MaxRadix, try to find good codelet
16294  //
16295  for(j=maxradix; j>=2; j--)
16296  {
16297  if( n%j==0 )
16298  {
16299  n1 = j;
16300  n2 = n/j;
16301  break;
16302  }
16303  }
16304 
16305  //
16306  // In case no good codelet was found,
16307  // try to factorize N into product of ANY primes.
16308  //
16309  if( n1*n2!=n )
16310  {
16311  for(j=2; j<=n-1; j++)
16312  {
16313  if( n%j==0 )
16314  {
16315  n1 = j;
16316  n2 = n/j;
16317  break;
16318  }
16319  if( j*j>n )
16320  {
16321  break;
16322  }
16323  }
16324  }
16325 
16326  //
16327  // normalize
16328  //
16329  if( n1>n2 )
16330  {
16331  j = n1;
16332  n1 = n2;
16333  n2 = j;
16334  }
16335  }
16336 
16337 
16338  /*************************************************************************
16339  Returns optimistic estimate of the FFT cost, in UNITs (1 UNIT = 100 KFLOPs)
16340 
16341  INPUT PARAMETERS:
16342  N - task size, N>0
16343 
16344  RESULU:
16345  cost in UNITs, rounded down to nearest integer
16346 
16347  NOTE: If FFT cost is less than 1 UNIT, it will return 0 as result.
16348 
16349  -- ALGLIB --
16350  Copyright 08.04.2013 by Bochkanov Sergey
16351  *************************************************************************/
16352  private static int ftoptimisticestimate(int n,
16353  alglib.xparams _params)
16354  {
16355  int result = 0;
16356 
16357  alglib.ap.assert(n>0, "FTOptimisticEstimate: N<=0");
16358  result = (int)Math.Floor(1.0E-5*5*n*Math.Log(n)/Math.Log(2));
16359  return result;
16360  }
16361 
16362 
16363  /*************************************************************************
16364  Twiddle factors calculation
16365 
16366  -- ALGLIB --
16367  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
16368  *************************************************************************/
16369  private static void ffttwcalc(double[] a,
16370  int aoffset,
16371  int n1,
16372  int n2,
16373  alglib.xparams _params)
16374  {
16375  int i = 0;
16376  int j2 = 0;
16377  int n = 0;
16378  int halfn1 = 0;
16379  int offs = 0;
16380  double x = 0;
16381  double y = 0;
16382  double twxm1 = 0;
16383  double twy = 0;
16384  double twbasexm1 = 0;
16385  double twbasey = 0;
16386  double twrowxm1 = 0;
16387  double twrowy = 0;
16388  double tmpx = 0;
16389  double tmpy = 0;
16390  double v = 0;
16391  int updatetw2 = 0;
16392 
16393 
16394  //
16395  // Multiplication by twiddle factors for complex Cooley-Tukey FFT
16396  // with N factorized as N1*N2.
16397  //
16398  // Naive solution to this problem is given below:
16399  //
16400  // > for K:=1 to N2-1 do
16401  // > for J:=1 to N1-1 do
16402  // > begin
16403  // > Idx:=K*N1+J;
16404  // > X:=A[AOffset+2*Idx+0];
16405  // > Y:=A[AOffset+2*Idx+1];
16406  // > TwX:=Cos(-2*Pi()*K*J/(N1*N2));
16407  // > TwY:=Sin(-2*Pi()*K*J/(N1*N2));
16408  // > A[AOffset+2*Idx+0]:=X*TwX-Y*TwY;
16409  // > A[AOffset+2*Idx+1]:=X*TwY+Y*TwX;
16410  // > end;
16411  //
16412  // However, there are exist more efficient solutions.
16413  //
16414  // Each pass of the inner cycle corresponds to multiplication of one
16415  // entry of A by W[k,j]=exp(-I*2*pi*k*j/N). This factor can be rewritten
16416  // as exp(-I*2*pi*k/N)^j. So we can replace costly exponentiation by
16417  // repeated multiplication: W[k,j+1]=W[k,j]*exp(-I*2*pi*k/N), with
16418  // second factor being computed once in the beginning of the iteration.
16419  //
16420  // Also, exp(-I*2*pi*k/N) can be represented as exp(-I*2*pi/N)^k, i.e.
16421  // we have W[K+1,1]=W[K,1]*W[1,1].
16422  //
16423  // In our loop we use following variables:
16424  // * [TwBaseXM1,TwBaseY] = [cos(2*pi/N)-1, sin(2*pi/N)]
16425  // * [TwRowXM1, TwRowY] = [cos(2*pi*I/N)-1, sin(2*pi*I/N)]
16426  // * [TwXM1, TwY] = [cos(2*pi*I*J/N)-1, sin(2*pi*I*J/N)]
16427  //
16428  // Meaning of the variables:
16429  // * [TwXM1,TwY] is current twiddle factor W[I,J]
16430  // * [TwRowXM1, TwRowY] is W[I,1]
16431  // * [TwBaseXM1,TwBaseY] is W[1,1]
16432  //
16433  // During inner loop we multiply current twiddle factor by W[I,1],
16434  // during outer loop we update W[I,1].
16435  //
16436  //
16437  alglib.ap.assert(updatetw>=2, "FFTTwCalc: internal error - UpdateTw<2");
16438  updatetw2 = updatetw/2;
16439  halfn1 = n1/2;
16440  n = n1*n2;
16441  v = -(2*Math.PI/n);
16442  twbasexm1 = -(2*math.sqr(Math.Sin(0.5*v)));
16443  twbasey = Math.Sin(v);
16444  twrowxm1 = 0;
16445  twrowy = 0;
16446  offs = aoffset;
16447  for(i=0; i<=n2-1; i++)
16448  {
16449 
16450  //
16451  // Initialize twiddle factor for current row
16452  //
16453  twxm1 = 0;
16454  twy = 0;
16455 
16456  //
16457  // N1-point block is separated into 2-point chunks and residual 1-point chunk
16458  // (in case N1 is odd). Unrolled loop is several times faster.
16459  //
16460  for(j2=0; j2<=halfn1-1; j2++)
16461  {
16462 
16463  //
16464  // Processing:
16465  // * process first element in a chunk.
16466  // * update twiddle factor (unconditional update)
16467  // * process second element
16468  // * conditional update of the twiddle factor
16469  //
16470  x = a[offs+0];
16471  y = a[offs+1];
16472  tmpx = x*(1+twxm1)-y*twy;
16473  tmpy = x*twy+y*(1+twxm1);
16474  a[offs+0] = tmpx;
16475  a[offs+1] = tmpy;
16476  tmpx = (1+twxm1)*twrowxm1-twy*twrowy;
16477  twy = twy+(1+twxm1)*twrowy+twy*twrowxm1;
16478  twxm1 = twxm1+tmpx;
16479  x = a[offs+2];
16480  y = a[offs+3];
16481  tmpx = x*(1+twxm1)-y*twy;
16482  tmpy = x*twy+y*(1+twxm1);
16483  a[offs+2] = tmpx;
16484  a[offs+3] = tmpy;
16485  offs = offs+4;
16486  if( (j2+1)%updatetw2==0 && j2<halfn1-1 )
16487  {
16488 
16489  //
16490  // Recalculate twiddle factor
16491  //
16492  v = -(2*Math.PI*i*2*(j2+1)/n);
16493  twxm1 = Math.Sin(0.5*v);
16494  twxm1 = -(2*twxm1*twxm1);
16495  twy = Math.Sin(v);
16496  }
16497  else
16498  {
16499 
16500  //
16501  // Update twiddle factor
16502  //
16503  tmpx = (1+twxm1)*twrowxm1-twy*twrowy;
16504  twy = twy+(1+twxm1)*twrowy+twy*twrowxm1;
16505  twxm1 = twxm1+tmpx;
16506  }
16507  }
16508  if( n1%2==1 )
16509  {
16510 
16511  //
16512  // Handle residual chunk
16513  //
16514  x = a[offs+0];
16515  y = a[offs+1];
16516  tmpx = x*(1+twxm1)-y*twy;
16517  tmpy = x*twy+y*(1+twxm1);
16518  a[offs+0] = tmpx;
16519  a[offs+1] = tmpy;
16520  offs = offs+2;
16521  }
16522 
16523  //
16524  // update TwRow: TwRow(new) = TwRow(old)*TwBase
16525  //
16526  if( i<n2-1 )
16527  {
16528  if( (i+1)%updatetw==0 )
16529  {
16530  v = -(2*Math.PI*(i+1)/n);
16531  twrowxm1 = Math.Sin(0.5*v);
16532  twrowxm1 = -(2*twrowxm1*twrowxm1);
16533  twrowy = Math.Sin(v);
16534  }
16535  else
16536  {
16537  tmpx = twbasexm1+twrowxm1*twbasexm1-twrowy*twbasey;
16538  tmpy = twbasey+twrowxm1*twbasey+twrowy*twbasexm1;
16539  twrowxm1 = twrowxm1+tmpx;
16540  twrowy = twrowy+tmpy;
16541  }
16542  }
16543  }
16544  }
16545 
16546 
16547  /*************************************************************************
16548  Linear transpose: transpose complex matrix stored in 1-dimensional array
16549 
16550  -- ALGLIB --
16551  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
16552  *************************************************************************/
16553  private static void internalcomplexlintranspose(double[] a,
16554  int m,
16555  int n,
16556  int astart,
16557  double[] buf,
16558  alglib.xparams _params)
16559  {
16560  int i_ = 0;
16561  int i1_ = 0;
16562 
16563  ffticltrec(a, astart, n, buf, 0, m, m, n, _params);
16564  i1_ = (0) - (astart);
16565  for(i_=astart; i_<=astart+2*m*n-1;i_++)
16566  {
16567  a[i_] = buf[i_+i1_];
16568  }
16569  }
16570 
16571 
16572  /*************************************************************************
16573  Recurrent subroutine for a InternalComplexLinTranspose
16574 
16575  Write A^T to B, where:
16576  * A is m*n complex matrix stored in array A as pairs of real/image values,
16577  beginning from AStart position, with AStride stride
16578  * B is n*m complex matrix stored in array B as pairs of real/image values,
16579  beginning from BStart position, with BStride stride
16580  stride is measured in complex numbers, i.e. in real/image pairs.
16581 
16582  -- ALGLIB --
16583  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
16584  *************************************************************************/
16585  private static void ffticltrec(double[] a,
16586  int astart,
16587  int astride,
16588  double[] b,
16589  int bstart,
16590  int bstride,
16591  int m,
16592  int n,
16593  alglib.xparams _params)
16594  {
16595  int i = 0;
16596  int j = 0;
16597  int idx1 = 0;
16598  int idx2 = 0;
16599  int m2 = 0;
16600  int m1 = 0;
16601  int n1 = 0;
16602 
16603  if( m==0 || n==0 )
16604  {
16605  return;
16606  }
16607  if( Math.Max(m, n)<=8 )
16608  {
16609  m2 = 2*bstride;
16610  for(i=0; i<=m-1; i++)
16611  {
16612  idx1 = bstart+2*i;
16613  idx2 = astart+2*i*astride;
16614  for(j=0; j<=n-1; j++)
16615  {
16616  b[idx1+0] = a[idx2+0];
16617  b[idx1+1] = a[idx2+1];
16618  idx1 = idx1+m2;
16619  idx2 = idx2+2;
16620  }
16621  }
16622  return;
16623  }
16624  if( n>m )
16625  {
16626 
16627  //
16628  // New partition:
16629  //
16630  // "A^T -> B" becomes "(A1 A2)^T -> ( B1 )
16631  // ( B2 )
16632  //
16633  n1 = n/2;
16634  if( n-n1>=8 && n1%8!=0 )
16635  {
16636  n1 = n1+(8-n1%8);
16637  }
16638  alglib.ap.assert(n-n1>0);
16639  ffticltrec(a, astart, astride, b, bstart, bstride, m, n1, _params);
16640  ffticltrec(a, astart+2*n1, astride, b, bstart+2*n1*bstride, bstride, m, n-n1, _params);
16641  }
16642  else
16643  {
16644 
16645  //
16646  // New partition:
16647  //
16648  // "A^T -> B" becomes "( A1 )^T -> ( B1 B2 )
16649  // ( A2 )
16650  //
16651  m1 = m/2;
16652  if( m-m1>=8 && m1%8!=0 )
16653  {
16654  m1 = m1+(8-m1%8);
16655  }
16656  alglib.ap.assert(m-m1>0);
16657  ffticltrec(a, astart, astride, b, bstart, bstride, m1, n, _params);
16658  ffticltrec(a, astart+2*m1*astride, astride, b, bstart+2*m1, bstride, m-m1, n, _params);
16659  }
16660  }
16661 
16662 
16663  /*************************************************************************
16664  Recurrent subroutine for a InternalRealLinTranspose
16665 
16666 
16667  -- ALGLIB --
16668  Copyright 01.05.2009 by Bochkanov Sergey
16669  *************************************************************************/
16670  private static void fftirltrec(ref double[] a,
16671  int astart,
16672  int astride,
16673  ref double[] b,
16674  int bstart,
16675  int bstride,
16676  int m,
16677  int n,
16678  alglib.xparams _params)
16679  {
16680  int i = 0;
16681  int j = 0;
16682  int idx1 = 0;
16683  int idx2 = 0;
16684  int m1 = 0;
16685  int n1 = 0;
16686 
16687  if( m==0 || n==0 )
16688  {
16689  return;
16690  }
16691  if( Math.Max(m, n)<=8 )
16692  {
16693  for(i=0; i<=m-1; i++)
16694  {
16695  idx1 = bstart+i;
16696  idx2 = astart+i*astride;
16697  for(j=0; j<=n-1; j++)
16698  {
16699  b[idx1] = a[idx2];
16700  idx1 = idx1+bstride;
16701  idx2 = idx2+1;
16702  }
16703  }
16704  return;
16705  }
16706  if( n>m )
16707  {
16708 
16709  //
16710  // New partition:
16711  //
16712  // "A^T -> B" becomes "(A1 A2)^T -> ( B1 )
16713  // ( B2 )
16714  //
16715  n1 = n/2;
16716  if( n-n1>=8 && n1%8!=0 )
16717  {
16718  n1 = n1+(8-n1%8);
16719  }
16720  alglib.ap.assert(n-n1>0);
16721  fftirltrec(ref a, astart, astride, ref b, bstart, bstride, m, n1, _params);
16722  fftirltrec(ref a, astart+n1, astride, ref b, bstart+n1*bstride, bstride, m, n-n1, _params);
16723  }
16724  else
16725  {
16726 
16727  //
16728  // New partition:
16729  //
16730  // "A^T -> B" becomes "( A1 )^T -> ( B1 B2 )
16731  // ( A2 )
16732  //
16733  m1 = m/2;
16734  if( m-m1>=8 && m1%8!=0 )
16735  {
16736  m1 = m1+(8-m1%8);
16737  }
16738  alglib.ap.assert(m-m1>0);
16739  fftirltrec(ref a, astart, astride, ref b, bstart, bstride, m1, n, _params);
16740  fftirltrec(ref a, astart+m1*astride, astride, ref b, bstart+m1, bstride, m-m1, n, _params);
16741  }
16742  }

16750  *************************************************************************/
16751  private static void ftbasefindsmoothrec(int n,

16758  if( seed>=n )

16770  }

16780  {
16781  public static double nulog1p(double x,
16782  alglib.xparams _params)
16783  {
16784  double result = 0;
16785  double z = 0;
16786  double lp = 0;
16787  double lq = 0;
16788 
16789  z = 1.0+x;
16790  if( (double)(z)<(double)(0.70710678118654752440) || (double)(z)>(double)(1.41421356237309504880) )
16791  {
16792  result = Math.Log(z);
16793  return result;
16794  }
16795  z = x*x;
16796  lp = 4.5270000862445199635215E-5;
16797  lp = lp*x+4.9854102823193375972212E-1;
16798  lp = lp*x+6.5787325942061044846969E0;
16799  lp = lp*x+2.9911919328553073277375E1;
16800  lp = lp*x+6.0949667980987787057556E1;
16801  lp = lp*x+5.7112963590585538103336E1;
16802  lp = lp*x+2.0039553499201281259648E1;
16803  lq = 1.0000000000000000000000E0;
16804  lq = lq*x+1.5062909083469192043167E1;
16805  lq = lq*x+8.3047565967967209469434E1;
16806  lq = lq*x+2.2176239823732856465394E2;
16807  lq = lq*x+3.0909872225312059774938E2;
16808  lq = lq*x+2.1642788614495947685003E2;
16809  lq = lq*x+6.0118660497603843919306E1;
16810  z = -(0.5*z)+x*(z*lp/lq);
16811  result = x+z;
16812  return result;
16813  }

16816  public static double nuexpm1(double x,
16817  alglib.xparams _params)
16818  {
16819  double result = 0;
16820  double r = 0;
16821  double xx = 0;
16822  double ep = 0;
16823  double eq = 0;
16824 
16825  if( (double)(x)<(double)(-0.5) || (double)(x)>(double)(0.5) )
16826  {
16827  result = Math.Exp(x)-1.0;
16828  return result;
16829  }
16830  xx = x*x;
16831  ep = 1.2617719307481059087798E-4;
16832  ep = ep*xx+3.0299440770744196129956E-2;
16833  ep = ep*xx+9.9999999999999999991025E-1;
16834  eq = 3.0019850513866445504159E-6;
16835  eq = eq*xx+2.5244834034968410419224E-3;
16836  eq = eq*xx+2.2726554820815502876593E-1;
16837  eq = eq*xx+2.0000000000000000000897E0;
16838  r = x*ep;
16839  r = r/(eq-r);
16840  result = r+r;
16841  return result;
16842  }

16845  public static double nucosm1(double x,
16846  alglib.xparams _params)
16847  {
16848  double result = 0;
16849  double xx = 0;
16850  double c = 0;
16851 
16852  if( (double)(x)<(double)(-(0.25*Math.PI)) || (double)(x)>(double)(0.25*Math.PI) )
16853  {
16854  result = Math.Cos(x)-1;
16855  return result;
16856  }
16857  xx = x*x;
16858  c = 4.7377507964246204691685E-14;
16859  c = c*xx-1.1470284843425359765671E-11;
16860  c = c*xx+2.0876754287081521758361E-9;
16861  c = c*xx-2.7557319214999787979814E-7;
16862  c = c*xx+2.4801587301570552304991E-5;
16863  c = c*xx-1.3888888888888872993737E-3;
16864  c = c*xx+4.1666666666666666609054E-2;
16865  result = -(0.5*xx)+xx*xx*c;
16866  return result;
